(53, 'Medicine and the Arts: Humanising Healthcare', 'Explore the field of medical humanities - the intersection of the arts, humanities and healthcare - with this free online course.', 'This free online course will explore the intersection of medicine, medical anthropology and the creative arts. Through each of its six weeks, we’ll visit a new aspect of human life and consider it from the perspectives of people working in health sciences, social sciences and the arts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/medicine-and-the-arts', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2400635.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ec/e2/regular_ece2817a-2a18-45b6-ac8a-774a4d2988e1.jpg', 'Media & Art', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Cape Town', '2015-11-04 00:00:52'),
(54, 'Much Ado about Nothing: in Performance', 'Explore how Much Ado about Nothing is performed and interpreted, from original stagings to the modern day, with this free course.', 'Shakespeare’s much loved play, Much Ado about Nothing, is read and studied all over the world. But it was written to be staged, and can only be fully appreciated and understood through performance.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/much-ado-about-nothing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2369693.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/48/a1/regular_48a12764-dbe4-4337-b76f-7ab4825706fd.jpg', 'Media & Art', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:00:53'),
(55, 'Physical Theatre: Meyerhold and Biomechanics', 'Learn how to practice Meyerhold’s biomechanics and study its place in the history of physical theatre.', 'This short three-week course introduces you to world-renowned Russian director Meyerhold’s technique of biomechanics, inviting you to experience first-hand his revolutionary approach to acting – the biomechanical études. You will learn about the techniques and find out more about the history of physical theatre including Meyerhold’s contribution to its development and how, nearly 100 years later, his work is still influencing us today.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/physical-theatre', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2197546.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/9c/24/regular_9c244de4-47ef-4310-9ca9-4734f5109ade.jpg', 'Media & Art', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:00:54'),
(56, 'Good Brain, Bad Brain: Drug Origins', 'Explore our past, present and future understanding of drugs with this free course. Where do drugs come from? How do they work?', 'This course is designed for anyone who has ever wondered how the drugs in their medicine cabinet were found in the first place and how they ended up as pills in a bottle.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/good-brain-bad-brain-drugs', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2389597.mp4', '2015-11-02', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/30/94/regular_3094e11c-a724-4785-8780-58eb71aed537.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:00:57'),
(57, 'Why Do We Age? The Molecular Mechanisms of Ageing', 'Why do we age? Is there a limit to human lifespan? Can we prolong our lives? Find out with this free online course.', 'The “why” and “how” of ageing has puzzled mankind ever since it questioned its place in the universe. However, it was only after infectious diseases became more controlled and reliable food supplies became generally available, that the rapid increase of the average lifespan made science turn its attention to study longevity and ageing.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ageing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3155756.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/2a/regular_422a2468-5da5-4fe4-85d9-bd78671b980c.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:00:58'),
(58, 'What is a Mind?', 'Explore the most pertinent scientific and philosophical concepts for understanding our own minds with this free online course', 'This free online course will bring together learners and practitioners interested in how the mind works. It aims to build bridges between traditionally antagonistic approaches to understanding the mind.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/what-is-a-mind', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2817852.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8a/dd/regular_8addb4ba-36d2-4d3c-a3d6-156bacd6690d.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Cape Town', '2015-11-04 00:00:58'),
(59, 'Improving Healthcare Through Clinical Research', 'Find out how medical treatments are discovered, tested and evaluated, to improve healthcare for all, on this free online course.', 'Everything we do in healthcare - every tablet that’s prescribed, every treatment that’s given and every test that’s performed - has to be first discovered and then thoroughly evaluated before it can be put into practice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/clinical-research', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5394540.mp4', '2015-11-02', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a8/e8/regular_a8e878c7-6b58-4e07-9895-ae0403ee7540.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:00:59'),
(60, 'The Mind is Flat: the Shocking Shallowness of Human Psychology', 'Make better personal and professional decisions, considering the psychological dimension to choices, with this free online course.', 'What are the forces shaping human behaviour? How do we think and decide? This course, from Professor Nick Chater and Warwick Business School, explores the origins of human rationality and irrationality.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-mind-is-flat', '', '2015-11-09', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/12/3e/regular_123ecc58-cdac-4e5f-84b0-64a2964fcfdf.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Warwick', '2015-11-04 00:00:59'),
(61, 'Global Blindness: Planning and Managing Eye Care Services', 'Understand global blindness and how to plan effective eye care with this free online course for health professionals', 'Around the world, 285 million people are blind or visually impaired. 75% of this is avoidable and 90% is in low- and middle-income countries.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/global-blindness', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2956886.mp4', '2015-11-09', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a3/af/regular_a3af1913-e926-4f89-a9b1-93b7911f7212.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine', '2015-11-04 00:01:00'),
(62, 'The Genomics Era: the Future of Genetics in Medicine', 'Learn about the growing role of genomics in healthcare, for patient diagnoses and treatment, with this free online course', 'This free online course will provide healthcare professionals with a basic grounding in genomic medicine. It will introduce you to the new genomic technologies that are revolutionising medicine and will, in time, provide the mainstay of patient diagnosis, treatment and disease prevention.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-genomics-era', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3533489.mp4', '2015-11-09', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8c/a3/regular_8ca34745-2d02-450b-8b70-b0c635368251.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'St Georges, University of London', '2015-11-04 00:01:01'),
(63, 'Measuring and Valuing Health', 'Learn how Patient Reported Outcome Measures and Quality Adjusted Life Years can compare treatments and inform healthcare spending.', 'Healthcare systems around the world are increasingly under pressure to fund drugs, treatments and other healthcare interventions. No-one has the money or resources to provide them all, so how do we decide which ones to fund?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/valuing-health', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2389556.mp4', '2015-11-23', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/73/ff/regular_73ffffe7-2825-48fa-a20d-06136a97690f.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:01:02'),
(64, 'Bioprinting: 3D Printing Body Parts', 'Discover how biomaterials and 3D printing collide, to create revolutionary, bioprinted body parts, with this free online course.', 'You may be aware of 3D printing or have seen low-cost 3D printers, which can create plastic toys, replicas and objects of your own design. But did you know that 3D printing is also enabling life-saving and transforming medical procedures, which were unthinkable a few years ago?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/bioprinting', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4894894.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e6/3f/regular_e63f6908-c6bc-4bc2-9059-d18064cac286.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Australian Institute for Innovative Materials, University of Wollongong ', '2015-11-04 00:01:02'),
(65, 'Clinical Supervision with Confidence', 'This course is designed to enhance the supervision skills of clinical and educational supervisors of trainee doctors.', 'Supervise medical students and trainees effectively with this free online course, ideal for clinical and educational supervisors.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/clinical-supervision-with-confidence', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2770835.mp4', '2015-11-30', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/13/16/regular_1316832d-7559-4531-b7f1-86742825ad34.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:01:03'),
(66, 'Social Media in Healthcare: Opportunities and Challenges', 'Understand how social media is used in healthcare, to improve communication and information sharing, with this free online course.', 'Social media has emerged as a new channel for both seeking information, and for creating and exchanging user-generated content among peers.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/social-media-in-healthcare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5435393.mp4', '2015-11-30', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e4/96/regular_e4961de7-feb1-455e-8114-c9471a3027f9.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Taipei Medical University', '2015-11-04 00:01:04'),
(67, 'Cancer in the 21st Century: the Genomic Revolution', 'Discover how genetics is revolutionising the detection and treatment of cancer, with this free online course.', 'Cancer Research UK estimates that 1 in 2 people in the UK will be diagnosed with cancer during their lifetime. It is a disease that impacts on most people’s lives at some stage. So understanding cancer, and the development of new treatments, is of intrinsic interest to us all.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cancer-and-the-genomic-revolution', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2958909.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/90/6f/regular_906f023f-dbe3-40ee-a8f5-2feb04c56828.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Glasgow', '2015-11-04 00:01:05'),
(68, 'Heart Health: a Beginners Guide to Cardiovascular Disease', 'Learn more about how your heart works, the causes of heart disease and how to keep your heart healthy with this free online course', 'Your heart beats around 100,000 times a day, pumping blood around your body to deliver oxygen and nutrients, while taking away waste products.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/heart-health', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3123756.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d4/fb/regular_d4fbef68-f45c-4b02-a1f4-a69d2a49f599.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:01:05');
INSERT INTO `course_data` (`id`, `title`, `short_desc`, `long_desc`, `course_link`, `video_link`, `start_date`, `course_length`, `course_image`, `category`, `site`, `course_fee`, `language`, `certificate`, `university`, `time_scraped`) VALUES
(69, 'Caring for Vulnerable Children', 'Develop an understanding of some of the approaches involved in caring for vulnerable children, with this free online course.', 'In times of austerity and shrinking public services, the task of identifying and caring for vulnerable children has never been more challenging. In this free online course, we’ll help you explore some of the issues involved in undertaking this task.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/vulnerable-children', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3154669.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a1/66/regular_a166c8fd-863d-45ee-b7e1-6b47ca5ace16.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Strathclyde', '2015-11-04 00:01:05'),
(70, 'The Science of Nutrition', 'Explore the science behind what you eat with this free online course.', 'Are we really what we eat? And how do we know what is in our food?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-nutrition', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4686390.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/98/c1/regular_98c184c3-0cff-44b6-87dd-fe341fc2a65a.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:01:06'),
(71, 'Liver Transplant: the Ins and Outs', 'Learn about the science behind having a liver transplant with this free online course from the Centre for Liver Research.', 'In this free, three-week course, we will teach you about the fascinating field of liver transplantation. We will cover the history of liver transplantation - from early experiments in the late 1960s to exciting new technological advances in organ preservation happening today.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/liver-transplant', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5282317.mp4', '2016-01-11', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/eb/06/regular_eb06d3a2-6c2f-42af-bec9-fb63f240ed94.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:01:07'),
(72, 'Nutrition and Wellbeing', 'Demystify the complex and conflicting messages we hear about nutrition, health and lifestyle today, with this free online course.', 'This free online course will help you understand the scientific basis of human nutrition, and current nutrition concepts and controversies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/nutrition-wellbeing', '', '2016-01-18', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2d/91/regular_2d918204-f6af-4bfe-8f44-90e5999d5cfb.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Aberdeen', '2015-11-04 00:01:07'),
(73, 'Influenza: How the Flu Spreads and Evolves', 'Get an introduction to the biology, epidemiology and evolution of the influenza virus in this free online course.', 'Influenza is a disease that strikes in two forms. Seasonal influenza returns each winter, killing up to half a million people in bad years and causing much misery. Pandemic influenza, by contrast, is rare - having occurred only a handful of times in the last century - and far worse than seasonal flu, often killing many millions across the world. The worst pandemic of all, the “Spanish Flu” of 1918, killed over twice as many people as the First World War - some estimates are even higher.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/influenza', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5438335.mp4', '2016-01-18', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/6a/b4/regular_6ab48a78-4da8-4719-80aa-e04bef2c3226.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'no', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:01:08'),
(74, 'Psychology and Mental Health: Beyond Nature and Nurture', 'Learn how a psychological understanding of our emotions and behaviour gives us new ways to improve mental health and well-being.', 'Psychological therapies and the work of clinical psychologists are now very popular. This free online course provides an introduction to how psychologists understand emotions, behaviours and thinking patterns, and how this helps clinical psychologists make sense of their clients’ problems.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/mental-health-and-well-being', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2647200.mp4', '2015-10-26', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/22/29/regular_2229c235-75ed-4f5d-b8da-90bc2f4c6506.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:01:09'),
(75, 'Liver Disease: Looking after Your Liver', 'Learn about how your liver works, ways to look after it and how liver damage is caused, studied and treated around the world.', 'We are currently experiencing an international explosion of liver disease that continues to have enormous impact upon healthcare systems and global health. In the UK we have seen a 20% increase in deaths related to liver disease since 2000 and this pattern reflects the global situation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/liver-disease', '', '2015-10-26', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/96/f4/regular_96f4c00f-5103-4ae4-a8c2-8b8485b3b651.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:01:09'),
(76, 'Exploring Play: The Importance of Play in Everyday Life', 'Understanding the nature and value of play through the course of our lives, across cultures and communities.', 'Play your part… Play the fool… All work and no play… Child’s play… Fair play… Play a joke… Play with fire…', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/play', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5053351.mp4', '2015-10-19', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/67/b9/regular_67b9b2fa-8b51-49bd-9327-005da7f4a2ef.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:01:10'),
(77, 'Babies in Mind: Why the Parents Mind Matters', 'Find out how parents and caregivers influence children’s minds, from conception through infancy, with this free online course.', 'This course will explore how the mind of the parent influences the developing mind of the child, from conception through infancy and into later life.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/babies-in-mind', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2708287.mp4', '2015-10-12', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/7e/regular_427e0a60-6c85-472d-bb71-1ff76f16e7ea.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Warwick', '2015-11-04 00:01:11'),
(78, 'Ultrasound Imaging: What Is Inside?', 'Understand the technology of ultrasound, see how it is used in clinical practice and learn how to improve medical imaging.', 'Ultrasound is an easy and quick technique to visualize structures inside the human body. It is a relatively harmless and accessible technique. It has been used for decades in medical practice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ultrasound-imaging', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4508377.mp4', '2015-10-05', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e1/39/regular_e1390375-f5b0-4893-9edf-3d36671ec508.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Twente', '2015-11-04 00:01:12'),
(79, 'Antimicrobial Stewardship: Managing Antibiotic Resistance', 'Understand antibiotic resistance, and how antimicrobial stewardship can slow down or reduce it, with this free online course', 'The World Health Organisation (WHO), when reporting on the escalating threat of antimicrobial resistance (AMR), warned that without urgent action, we’re heading for an era in which common infections, which have been treatable with antibiotics for decades, can kill once more. In some parts of the world, this sadly is already a reality.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/antimicrobial-stewardship', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3931380.mp4', '2015-09-28', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/91/f8/regular_91f873fd-8a2c-4336-b5c1-c876fba4d167.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Dundee', '2015-11-04 00:01:13'),
(80, 'Improving the Health of Women, Children and Adolescents: from Evidence to Action', 'Consider the latest data, priorities and debates about the health of mothers, children and adolescents in this free online course.', 'At a time of global concern over emerging infectious and chronic diseases, it is important to remember that millions of women and children continue to die every year from conditions that are easily preventable and treatable.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/women-children-health', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4446094.mp4', '2015-09-28', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/cf/72/regular_cf72faef-33da-48a6-b270-8f24c81ecdfc.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine', '2015-11-04 00:01:13'),
(81, 'Logical and Critical Thinking', 'Improve your logical and critical thinking skills in this free online course. Identify common obstacles to effective thinking.', 'We are constantly being given reasons to do and believe things: to believe that we should buy a product, support a cause, accept a job, judge someone innocent or guilty, that fairness requires us to do some household chore, and so on. Assessing the reasons we are given to do or believe these things calls upon us to think critically and logically.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/logical-and-critical-thinking', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4129686.mp4', '2015-09-28', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/5e/regular_a45e1791-4619-4c75-a5eb-98ee33da42b1.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Auckland', '2015-11-04 00:01:14'),
(82, 'Forensic Psychology: Witness Investigation', 'Discover how psychology can help obtain evidence from eyewitnesses in police investigations and prevent miscarriages of justice.', 'Explore how your own mind works, and discover how the limitations of the human brain can lead to major miscarriages of justice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/forensic-psychology', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2340401.mp4', '2015-09-14', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/bd/09/regular_bd0923f5-3b95-4cf4-b0b9-297a9706d19d.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:01:14'),
(83, 'Ageing Well: Falls', 'Explore why people fall, discover practical methods to reduce the risk of falling and recognise when to seek expert help.', 'Every day in the UK, almost 10,000 people aged over 65 will fall down. The personal costs are staggering, with falls resulting in injury, broken bones, fear of falling and social isolation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/falls', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2715981.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/47/c9/regular_47c90b98-8bb7-4fa5-9003-61f9befb0275.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Newcastle University', '2015-11-04 00:01:15'),
(84, 'Caring for People with Psychosis and Schizophrenia', 'Explore the key issues related to caring for a relative with psychosis or schizophrenia, with this short, free online course.', 'Psychosis conditions, including schizophrenia, are treatable mental health problems that can affect anyone although very few people talk about the conditions and their impact on families. Millions of people across the globe find themselves thrust unexpectedly into a role providing support and care when a relative develops psychosis. Carers can play a major role in supporting their relative’s progress and recovery.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/caring-psychosis-schizophrenia', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4716606.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/59/a6/regular_59a696d6-fa8c-4882-bf84-9c9eee396b66.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Kings College London', '2015-11-04 00:01:16'),
(85, 'Childhood in the Digital Age', 'Delve into the lives of children and discuss the potential benefits and limitations of technology in their lives.', 'Are you a technology optimist or a technology pessimist?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/childhood-in-the-digital-age', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4530272.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/14/f8/regular_14f8f7d0-c6ec-4d94-a99c-acff489aeb38.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:01:17'),
(86, 'Dysphagia: Swallowing Difficulties and Medicines', 'This course will enhance the knowledge of any person involved in the administration of medicines to patients with dysphagia.', 'The course offers an opportunity to network with other learners and with the creators of the course through discussions, graphs and social networking features and to share knowledge with other learners and professionals. By completing this online course participants will be able to describe:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dysphagia', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3261218.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/16/6c/regular_166c19c9-7eab-48da-b7b8-c21e383c1f58.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:01:18'),
(87, 'ECG Assessment: an Introduction for Healthcare Providers', 'Understand the principles of electrocardiography and learn a step-by-step approach to the ECG test, with this free online course.', 'The electrocardiograph (also known as electrocardiogram) or ECG is a non-invasive diagnostic procedure, commonly used to assess people with known or suspected heart disease, in a variety of healthcare settings.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ecg-assessment', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4640723.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/09/4c/regular_094c2fba-0a16-4965-a176-bd6daeb231f9.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'St Georges, University of London', '2015-11-04 00:01:19'),
(88, 'Ebola in Context: Understanding Transmission, Response and Control', 'How has the Ebola outbreak become a humanitarian emergency? Learn about the science behind the crisis.', 'In 2014, Ebola went from a scarcely known virus to the subject of daily news reports. The epidemic in West Africa has quickly surpassed all previous outbreaks, to become an unprecedented humanitarian crisis.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ebola-in-context', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2714612.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/46/1b/regular_461b7c93-fba6-4151-a140-cbdf9422c2bf.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine', '2015-11-04 00:01:19'),
(89, 'Ebola: Symptoms, History and Origins', 'Learn about Ebola, its symptoms, where it came from and what the current outbreak has taught us, with this free online course.', 'In December 2013, the largest outbreak of Ebola virus disease (EVD) that the world has ever seen, began in West Africa - a region of the continent that has historically been free of it.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ebola', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3089045.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d9/5e/regular_d95ef0b5-c747-4815-bcde-26ebc3d0f87d.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:01:20'),
(90, 'Exploring Anatomy: the Human Abdomen', 'Explore the anatomy of the human abdomen and understand its clinical importance.', 'This course introduces you to the human abdomen and explores its many complex structures. As the course progresses, the structure and function of important organs will be demonstrated, discussed and related to common surgical scenarios and current research. Each of the three weeks will focus on a specific area of the abdomen; starting at the surface you will then enter the abdomen and be able to detail the anatomy of numerous organs including the stomach and liver.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/anatomy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2321495.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0c/d4/regular_0cd42bec-6ea7-425f-9306-c84c455c8c6f.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:01:20'),
(91, 'Good Brain, Bad Brain: Basics', 'What do we know and what are we discovering about the form and function of the human brain? Find out with this free online course', 'This free online course is an introduction to the key concepts of the human brain and is designed for the non-specialist. It gives you basic information and explanations, so that you may better understand your own amazing brain.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/good-brain-bad-brain-basics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2882955.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/69/6c/regular_696ca98e-c62a-4be3-8654-adb47abb2167.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:01:21'),
(92, 'Good Brain, Bad Brain: Parkinsons Disease', 'Learn the fundamentals of Parkinsons disease with this free online course. What causes it and what we can do to treat it?', 'This free online course is aimed at anyone who wants to find out the fundamentals of Parkinson’s disease. We will look at how Parkinson’s disease affects people; what causes it; what we can do to try to ameliorate the symptoms of Parkinson’s; and what we don’t yet know about it.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/good-brain-bad-brain-parkinsons', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1911387.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e6/01/regular_e601d52c-2f7b-4469-bf17-9bfa0b4ed3e6.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:01:22'),
(93, 'How to Read a Mind', 'How do we read and model fictional minds? Introducing cognitive poetics: the application of cognitive science to literary reading.', 'This course offers an introduction to what has come to be known as cognitive poetics. Taking our best current knowledge of how our minds and language work, this course takes you through key questions of literature and reading: why do we feel anything for fictional characters? Why do we get angry, moved, irritated, annoyed or sentimental about imaginary people in imagined worlds? Why do the lives of imaginary minds living in fictional bodies seem to matter so much to readers? The answers to these questions are surprising and empowering.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/how-to-read-a-mind', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/46/db/regular_46db5b59-369d-4663-a6e6-9f873f6117d1.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:01:22'),
(94, 'Inside Cancer: How Genes Influence Cancer Development', 'Understand how genetics influence the development and spread of cancer, with this free, introductory online course.', 'Cancer is a disease that affects around one-third of the human population, irrespective of nationality or ethnic origins. There are many types of cancer, but they all have one thing in common - they begin as rebel or mutant cells.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/inside-cancer', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2285126.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/17/73/regular_1773392a-c546-49f6-b52a-bee15ce2a57a.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bath', '2015-11-04 00:01:23'),
(95, 'Medicine and the Arts: Humanising Healthcare', 'Explore the field of medical humanities - the intersection of the arts, humanities and healthcare - with this free online course.', 'This free online course will explore the intersection of medicine, medical anthropology and the creative arts. Through each of its six weeks, we’ll visit a new aspect of human life and consider it from the perspectives of people working in health sciences, social sciences and the arts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/medicine-and-the-arts', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2400635.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ec/e2/regular_ece2817a-2a18-45b6-ac8a-774a4d2988e1.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Cape Town', '2015-11-04 00:01:24'),
(96, 'Medicines Adherence: Supporting Patients with their Treatment', 'How can healthcare professionals help patients to improve their health through medicines adherence?', 'It is estimated that 30-50% of patients do not take their medicines as prescribed. So how should we, as healthcare professionals, respond? As medicines are key to the successful management of chronic conditions, underuse or non-adherence represents a lost opportunity for the health improvement for the patient as well as being a waste of valuable resources for healthcare systems. In Europe alone, the cost of poor adherence to treatment is estimated at 195,000 lives and €20 billion annually.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/medicinesadherence', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1697242.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ba/98/regular_ba980fde-35b9-4e6a-b2d5-c6241c905570.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Kings College London', '2015-11-04 00:01:24'),
(97, 'Metabolomics: Understanding Metabolism in the 21st Century', 'Discover how metabolomics is revolutionising our understanding of metabolism with this free online course.', 'Metabolomics is an emerging field that aims to measure the complement of metabolites (the intermediates and products of metabolism) in living organisms. The complement of metabolites in a biological system is known as the metabolome and represents the downstream effect of an organism’s genome and its interaction with the environment. Metabolomics has a wide application area across the medical and biological sciences and is attractive to both new and established scientists. In this course we will provide an introduction to metabolomics, explain why we want to study the metabolome and describe the current challenges in analysing the complement of metabolites in a biological system. We will describe the interdisciplinary approaches adopted in the metabolomics workflow and demonstrate how the combined efforts of scientist’s from different disciplines is advancing this exciting field. By the end of the course the learner will understand how metabolomics can revolutionise our understanding of metabolism.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/metabolomics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4782792.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e3/84/regular_e384a622-583e-4778-b412-78614e422023.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:01:25'),
(98, 'Mindfulness for Wellbeing and Peak Performance', 'Learn mindfulness techniques to reduce stress and improve your wellbeing and work/study performance in this free online course.', 'Tired, distracted and stressed by the pace of modern life? Mindfulness might be the solution.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/mindfulness-wellbeing-performance', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4121262.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0f/26/regular_0f26d495-f407-4254-90ae-0d7970cb1fbb.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:01:26'),
(99, 'Obesity: Causes and Consequences', 'Obesity is a global epidemic. As the world gets fatter, explore its impact on our health and lives, with this free online course.', 'Obesity is changing the world we live in. Across a wide range of sectors - from the food industry to clothing design - we see the impact of the world’s growing waistline.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/obesity', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2326776.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1f/f8/regular_1ff8c595-917b-4bec-b2c6-90dd4e26cf77.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:01:26'),
(100, 'The Impact of Nursing', 'Take a journey from the past to the future of nursing with this free online course. Explore nursing’s impact on quality of life.', 'Health is the most important thing we have, and nurses are at the forefront of healthcare delivery in a rapidly changing world. This is a central message of this free online course, which takes you on a journey from the past to the future of nursing.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-impact-of-nursing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2493409.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/27/1f/regular_271fc1a4-7774-4c67-a053-0671f109149c.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:01:27'),
(101, 'The Informed Health Consumer: Making Sense of Evidence', 'How do you understand whether health evidence is likely to be reliable or not? Find out in this free online course.', 'Every day we read or hear about new health research that looks at what might help or harm, limit or extend our lives. Health research is big business and over a million papers are now published annually on health-related topics. So how do we find the evidence we need and, much more important, how do we judge how good that evidence is?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/informed-health-consumer', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4811294.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d7/f7/regular_d7f76ddb-b2e0-4c95-8295-43aa5faee90c.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Cardiff University', '2015-11-04 00:01:28'),
(102, 'The Science of Medicines', 'Learn the science behind how and why medicines work, and what can improve patients treatment, with this free online course.', 'The world’s growing population faces major health issues, and medicines are a primary pillar to effect better health. Learn about the science of key medicines used to manage heart disease, depression, diabetes, pain control and smoking cessation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-medicines', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a3/2d/regular_a32d14b8-c30d-4218-b151-b0a596206f68.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:01:28'),
(103, 'Understanding Drugs and Addiction', 'How do addictions develop? How are they best treated and prevented? Explore these key questions with this free online course.', 'We are all touched by addiction – personally, within our circle of family and friends, and within our community. Addiction and its related harms can be crippling for those affected and the people around them.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/understanding-drugs-and-addiction', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2378628.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1f/e2/regular_1fe271ce-ad9f-4bc4-85e0-d61816b21ca0.jpg', 'Health & Psychology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Kings College London', '2015-11-04 00:01:29'),
(104, 'Hadrians Wall: Life on the Roman Frontier', 'Explore the archaeology of the most heavily fortified frontier in the Roman Empire, its people and their lives.', 'Explore the archaeology of the most heavily fortified frontier in the Roman Empire, its people and their lives.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/hadrians-wall', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2317804.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fe/a9/regular_fea9b9a3-bed1-4ec2-9af6-ba1148e29aea.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Newcastle University', '2015-11-04 00:01:30'),
(105, 'Empire: the Controversies of British Imperialism', 'The British Empire continues to cause enormous disagreement among historians. Find out why and join the debate.', 'The British Empire was the largest empire ever seen. It ruled over a quarter of the world’s population and paved the way for today’s global economy. But British imperialism isn’t without controversy, and it continues to cause enormous disagreement among historians today.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/empire', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4483092.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0b/35/regular_0b35ad61-2228-424d-ab31-0df605e4dad4.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Exeter', '2015-11-04 00:01:31'),
(106, 'The Holocaust: an Introduction - Part 1', 'Part 1 of 2. This course depicts the complex history of the Holocaust, highlighting its impact on our world today.', 'The Holocaust was an inconceivable historical event, which forever robbed Western culture of its innocence. As civilized human beings, we fail to understand how events of such horror could have taken place, and how an idea so inhumanly warped could have spread like wildfire through an entire continent, instigating the systematic annihilation of millions of Jews.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/holocaust-part-1', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5064644.mp4', '2015-11-02', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f1/ba/regular_f1ba6945-f327-41ca-b7a3-129cdccf8fa8.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Tel Aviv University', '2015-11-04 00:01:32'),
(107, 'World War 1: Trauma and Memory', 'Discover the traumatic effects of war on those who survive it, from the soldiers on the front lines to the civilians at home.', '2014 marks the centennial year of the beginning of World War 1. The war began in the Balkans, but it soon spread to become a European conflict, and developed into a world war.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-trauma', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2181981.mp4', '2015-11-16', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d6/f1/regular_d6f1438f-b787-4d7b-ba24-2aa657549592.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:01:33'),
(108, 'The Holocaust: an Introduction - Part 2', 'Part 2 of 2. This course depicts the complex history of the Holocaust, highlighting its impact on our world today.', 'The Holocaust was an inconceivable historical event, which forever robbed Western culture of its innocence. As civilized human beings, we fail to understand how events of such horror could have taken place, and how an idea so inhumanly warped could have spread like wildfire through an entire continent, instigating the systematic annihilation of millions of Jews.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/holocaust-part-2', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5065337.mp4', '2015-11-30', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a0/10/regular_a0103679-8ee3-45e7-8d3d-653d093aa56c.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Tel Aviv University', '2015-11-04 00:01:34'),
(109, 'Exploring English: Magna Carta', 'Improve your English language skills while exploring the Magna Carta - the 800-year-old "great charter" that shaped the world.', 'How did a peace treaty signed by an English king in 1215 become such an important symbol of liberty and human rights around the world?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/explore-english-magna-carta', '', '2015-11-30', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/9b/3f/regular_9b3f3036-7191-4f53-8aea-db43abe85b28.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:01:35'),
(110, 'World War 1: Lessons and Legacy of the Great War', 'Learn how the Allies defeat the Germans in World War 1, how the memory arose that the war was futile, and why this view is untrue.', 'What is your understanding of World War I? Brave men led to their deaths by stupid officers? A war of trenches, mud and barbed wire in which there was no victor?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-lessons-legacy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5356990.mp4', '2016-02-08', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e1/4a/regular_e14ae70f-bd1a-47d8-b50d-adc5a53d0c61.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:01:35'),
(111, 'Military Ethics: An Introduction', 'We explore the ethical responsibilities that weigh on military professionals, who are ‘managers of violence’.', 'Military professionals are unusual in having the use of lethal force as a central, defining feature of their role, and unique in the level of force that they are authorized to use. This fact places a considerable ethical weight on military practitioners as well as the civilian decision-makers who authorize military missions.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/military-ethics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5387660.mp4', '2016-02-29', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f2/02/regular_f2020743-f023-4d3a-bac1-fafa5907d58f.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:01:36'),
(112, 'World War 1: Changing Faces of Heroism', 'Learn how the war moved us away from traditional views of heroism and created new kinds of heroes and heroines.', 'Did World War 1 make heroism meaningless or was it the conflict that gave it the most meaning? We’ve designed this course in partnership with the BBC to help you explore, discuss and challenge the ways in which World War 1 heroism has been remembered. Our experts will take you through the changing British, French and German views of heroism and discuss important similarities and differences.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-heroism', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3053661.mp4', '2015-10-26', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/40/b5/regular_40b5ca70-dc9c-4f4f-8a13-c75f40ba818d.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:01:37'),
(113, 'World War 1: A History in 100 Stories', 'Change the way you see World War 1 as you explore stories of hope, suffering and loss from newly released historical archives.', 'The Gallipoli Campaign was Australia and New Zealand’s first major military engagement of World War 1. The Anzacs went on to fight in Palestine, Egypt and the Western Front and suffered one of the highest casualty rates of any allied army.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-stories', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2377019.mp4', '2015-10-12', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/6c/regular_426c9a51-9278-47d3-b64f-408dfe3d2e88.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:01:38'),
(114, 'The European Discovery of China', 'Explore Chinese history through the eyes of Western travellers, discoverers and missionaries, with this free online course.', 'This free online course focuses on when and how the West first approached China. We will explore the influence that the discovery of China exerted on late medieval and early modern European minds.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/european-discovery-china', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3990564.mp4', '2015-09-28', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/71/04/regular_7104226d-9edf-44b2-8bb4-956bebc969aa.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Pompeu Fabra University Barcelona', '2015-11-04 00:01:39'),
(115, 'Agincourt 1415: Myth and Reality', 'Mark the 600th anniversary of the Battle of Agincourt, exploring its history and legacy, with this free online course.', 'The Battle of Agincourt, in 1415, is one of the most famous battles in the history of warfare, and one of the most important and memorable English victories. It still captures the imagination today, but why are stories still told about Agincourt? And do these stories represent what really happened on the battlefield?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/agincourt', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4941171.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b4/72/regular_b472bf65-1df2-413f-95d6-b5b7bc0b2af3.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:01:40'),
(116, 'Archaeology of Portus: Exploring the Lost Harbour of Ancient Rome', 'Learn how ancient artefacts, written evidence, excavation and digital technologies are transforming understanding of this harbour.', 'The Roman harbour city of Portus lay at the heart of an empire that extended from Scotland to Iraq. Established by Claudius and enlarged by the emperor Trajan with spoils of the Dacian wars, the port was the conduit for everything the city of Rome required from its Mediterranean provinces: the food and, particularly grain, that fed the largest urban population of the ancient world, as well as luxuries of all kinds, building materials, people and wild animals for the arena.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/portus', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4432688.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/08/9e/regular_089eb0ae-3947-41b1-9efe-7d03adf06bac.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:01:41'),
(117, 'England in the Time of King Richard III', 'Explore 15th century England through archaeology, history and literature. Learn more about Richard III’s discovery and reburial.', 'The discovery of the skeleton of Richard III in a Leicester car park - and the recent revelations of an infidelity within his family’s bloodline - have made headline news around the world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/england-of-richard-third', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3043326.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fc/e8/regular_fce85c43-556f-400a-9386-d122b8c467c3.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leicester', '2015-11-04 00:01:41'),
(118, 'Irish Lives in War and Revolution: Exploring Irelands History 1912-1923', 'Explore the lives of men, women and children living through war and revolution and social changes that made modern Ireland.', 'How do people experience war and revolution? How does political change, violence, total war, affect life in its most basic ways?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/irish-history', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2340437.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fd/b0/regular_fdb03c53-4926-4090-a68b-1d000f1a8348.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Trinity College Dublin', '2015-11-04 00:01:42'),
(119, 'Lips and Teeth: Korea and China in Modern Times', 'Explore the historical evolution of China and the Korean Peninsula and discover the implications for today.', 'As countries across Asia - and the globe - wrestle with the impact of China’s rise, nowhere are the opportunities and threats of a wealthy and powerful China felt more keenly than next door, on the Korean Peninsula.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/korea-and-china', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2419110.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/60/5e/regular_605e0239-009a-451d-aa14-57eee58b3259.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Yonsei University', '2015-11-04 00:01:43'),
(120, 'Modern Korean History: Liberation, War and Nuclear Ambitions', 'Explore the unique and untold history of North and South Korea - from 1945 to the present - with this free online course.', 'The contemporary history of the Korean peninsula has been a tumultuous tale of decolonization, war and rapid economic development. Both North and South Korea has had an immense impact on the world stage and today many wonder why this region of East Asia appears so frequently in the international news.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/modern-korean-history', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2372067.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ff/51/regular_ff5143af-a195-45ae-9e42-aff3857da80e.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Yonsei University', '2015-11-04 00:01:44'),
(121, 'Propaganda and Ideology in Everyday Life', 'Find out how propaganda is used to instil political ideologies and its impact on our daily lives, with this free online course.', 'This free online course explores the building blocks of our political views: freedom, community, place, justice and choice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/propaganda', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2801553.mp4', '0000-00-00', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/23/regular_ef2351cc-cde8-4ed0-9801-4bfc380e0930.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:01:44'),
(122, 'Superpowers of the Ancient World: the Near East', 'Experience the world’s first international age, 3,500 years ago in the ancient Near East, with this free online course.', 'Over four weeks, this free online course explores four ancient Near-Eastern cultures and how they interacted with each other 3,500 years ago.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/superpowers-near-east', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4115194.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/33/8c/regular_338c724e-a5c0-4318-a826-0d253678383d.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:01:45'),
(123, 'Wellington and the Battle of Waterloo', 'Mark the bicentenary of the Battle of Waterloo in 2015 and explore the Duke of Wellington’s archive with this free online course.', 'The Battle of Waterloo was one of the key events of nineteenth-century history, but why was it fought, who was involved and what were consequences? This free online course will answer these questions, marking the 200th anniversary of Waterloo on 18 June 2015.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/wellington-and-waterloo', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3618045.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b7/09/regular_b70934ab-3aa0-49d0-bef4-65a71b896686.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:01:46'),
(124, 'World War 1: Aviation Comes of Age', 'Investigate how the white heat of innovation in World War 1 shaped the history of human flight.', 'Investigate how the early days of aviation gripped the imagination of the general public, galvanised industry and excited far-sighted members of the military, with this free online course from the University of Birmingham’s Centre for War Studies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-aviation', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3340918.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/09/4b/regular_094bbaf9-ed37-4ba6-8bf0-5f83f47471e9.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:01:46'),
(125, 'World War 1: Paris 1919 - A New World Order?', 'This course reassesses the legacy of the Paris Peace Conference (1919) and how it sought to create a new world order.', 'The Paris Peace Conference of 1919 ended a Great War, but it also designed the post-war future. In 1919, world leaders assembled in Paris redrew the map of the world, partitioned and created countries, and ushered in a new era of international relations. The naivety of the peace-makers of 1919 has been justly criticised. However, in setting up a permanent ‘world organisation’, the League of Nations, they changed the management of world affairs forever.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-new-world-order', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2196589.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/23/7e/regular_237e6c99-3f52-4853-96e0-bafa0e3dfdd1.jpg', 'History', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Glasgow', '2015-11-04 00:01:47'),
(126, 'Introduction to Dutch', 'Learn to speak, write and understand basic Dutch, with this free, three-week, introductory foreign language course.', 'Are you planning to visit, or work or study in the Netherlands soon? This free online course is perfect if you have little or no prior knowledge of Dutch, but would like to master the fundamentals in order to survive life in the Low Countries.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dutch', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2912826.mp4', '2015-11-02', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/29/24/regular_2924bac4-50c7-4855-80b9-32894b3635ef.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:01:50'),
(127, 'Intercultural Communication', 'Learn to appreciate, adjust to, and work or study in different cultures, with this free online intercultural communication course.', 'Whether you’re engaging in business across borders or cultural regions, meeting other people through international travel, working in a diverse, global organisation or studying abroad, you can benefit from a better understanding of intercultural communication.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/intercultural-communication', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5346186.mp4', '2015-11-09', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/73/7e/regular_737e6fa1-bed3-4711-b089-cc21677a10e8.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Shanghai International Studies University (SISU)', '2015-11-04 00:01:51'),
(128, 'Exploring English: Magna Carta', 'Improve your English language skills while exploring the Magna Carta - the 800-year-old "great charter" that shaped the world.', 'How did a peace treaty signed by an English king in 1215 become such an important symbol of liberty and human rights around the world?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/explore-english-magna-carta', '', '2015-11-30', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/9b/3f/regular_9b3f3036-7191-4f53-8aea-db43abe85b28.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:01:51'),
(129, 'Exploring English: Shakespeare', 'Improve your English language skills by looking at the life and works of William Shakespeare and his enduring popularity.', 'This free online course will look at the life and works of William Shakespeare and take you from his Birthplace in Stratford-upon-Avon to the Globe Theatre in London, from where he secured his central place in English literature.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/explore-english-shakespeare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5517695.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/df/30/regular_df30152c-3fd2-4f96-a151-a39fcead4da3.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:01:52'),
(130, 'A Beginners Guide to Writing in English for University Study', 'Learn how to use English for study at university or college and develop your writing skills, vocabulary and grammar.', 'If you’re interested in studying at university or college in an English-speaking country, you’ll need to learn how to write using academic English. Academic writing can be very different from other types of English writing you may have done in the past. We have developed this course to help you learn the basics of academic writing and develop your English skills for study in the UK, US, Australia or other countries where English is used.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/english-for-study', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2840424.mp4', '2016-01-18', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a7/4c/regular_a74c84a4-b484-4372-ae31-4db7c100529b.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:01:53'),
(131, 'Exploring English: Language and Culture', 'This course for learners of English looks at British culture and examines English in use to help you improve your language skills.', 'This course is for people who are learning English and who are interested in finding out more about British culture and improving their English language skills.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/explore-english-language-culture', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3031601.mp4', '2015-10-19', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ab/54/regular_ab54c18c-fe97-4b06-aee1-7ef578503e9f.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:01:53'),
(132, 'Understanding Language: Learning and Teaching', 'An introduction to some key concepts in the effective teaching and learning of languages.', 'What is language? How do we learn meaning in a new language? What is easy and hard about learning another language? And what is the best way to teach other languages?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/understanding-language', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2497255.mp4', '2015-10-12', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8d/f5/regular_8df536e7-bcbf-45eb-8599-d8aa0da56616.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:01:54'),
(133, 'Cultural Studies and Modern Languages: an Introduction', 'Explore the culture, language and national identity of eight countries through their books, images, slogans and monuments', 'Are you interested in other countries? Do you want to study and understand other cultures? This free online course will take you on a journey through a number of periods from the medieval to the modern day, from Russia to Europe and all the way to Latin America.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cultural-studies', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428991.mp4', '2015-09-28', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b5/c7/regular_b5c7c300-3189-4c96-ae66-597a6192c138.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bristol', '2015-11-04 00:01:55');
INSERT INTO `course_data` (`id`, `title`, `short_desc`, `long_desc`, `course_link`, `video_link`, `start_date`, `course_length`, `course_image`, `category`, `site`, `course_fee`, `language`, `certificate`, `university`, `time_scraped`) VALUES
(134, 'Corpus Linguistics: Method, Analysis, Interpretation', 'Offers practical introduction to the methodology of corpus linguistics for researchers in social sciences and humanities', 'The course aims to:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/corpus-linguistics', '', '2015-09-28', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/33/9f/regular_339ff074-1f50-4a77-a9d8-822cf939be13.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:01:56'),
(135, 'The European Discovery of China', 'Explore Chinese history through the eyes of Western travellers, discoverers and missionaries, with this free online course.', 'This free online course focuses on when and how the West first approached China. We will explore the influence that the discovery of China exerted on late medieval and early modern European minds.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/european-discovery-china', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3990564.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/71/04/regular_7104226d-9edf-44b2-8bb4-956bebc969aa.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Pompeu Fabra University Barcelona', '2015-11-04 00:01:57'),
(136, 'Dyslexia and Foreign Language Teaching', 'Gain practical tools and theoretical insights to help dyslexic students learn second languages, with this free online course.', 'Dyslexia affects 10-15% of the population. Dyslexic students are often either exempted from the study of additional languages or they underperform in foreign language classes.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dyslexia', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2555787.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/67/6c/regular_676cb58f-d5b5-4b13-9aa1-7b8bb2477e99.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:01:57'),
(137, 'Muslims in Britain: Changes and Challenges', 'Develop your understanding of Muslims and their faith through an exploration of communities in Britain.', 'Islam is the second largest religion in the world today and dominates much of the current geopolitical discourse. People are increasingly bombarded by dramatic and at times disturbing headlines. Yet general knowledge of Muslims and their faith can be poor. There is consequently a need for a balanced and well-informed understanding of the current debates around this internationally significant topic.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/muslims-in-britain', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2296530.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d8/1a/regular_d81a635c-cda9-41d4-b9aa-8b7d997970dc.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Cardiff University', '2015-11-04 00:01:58'),
(138, 'Professional Practices for English Language Teaching', 'A free online continuing professional development (CPD) course for people who are teaching English as a foreign language.', 'This free online course is for English language teachers around the world. It will help you develop the skills and practices you need for your continuing professional development (CPD).', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/english-language-teaching', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a9/cf/regular_a9cf89ec-1531-4cfe-839c-a23cbabfdea2.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:01:58'),
(139, 'Understanding IELTS: Techniques for English Language Tests', 'Improve your English and prepare for tests, such as IELTS reading, writing, speaking and listening, with this free online course.', 'Anyone thinking about taking an English language test, such as IELTS, will find this course particularly useful, but all English language learners will benefit from the tips and advice given in the course.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/understanding-ielts', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a2/a5/regular_a2a50e02-4364-4ef7-9353-32ce4fda2f09.jpg', 'Culture & Language', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:01:59'),
(140, 'Antiquities Trafficking and Art Crime', 'Delve into the seedy underbelly of the art world, looking at smuggling, theft, fakes, and fraud, with this free online course.', 'The devastation caused by the trafficking of illicit antiquities and the theft of art has gained widespread public attention in recent years.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/art-crime', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5348091.mp4', '2016-02-01', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a0/fd/regular_a0fd2545-9657-4fa4-9769-f4f910c9d9b7.jpg', 'Law', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Glasgow', '2015-11-04 00:02:01'),
(141, 'Crime, Justice and Society', 'Explore the role of the state and criminal justice interventions in producing safe and just societies', 'Crime and criminal justice are vast and fascinating issues that highlight the complexity of defining and solving social problems.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/crime-justice-society', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4928778.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/08/regular_a4085e9b-8156-4c36-b135-378813639661.jpg', 'Law', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:02:02'),
(142, 'Forensic Psychology: Witness Investigation', 'Discover how psychology can help obtain evidence from eyewitnesses in police investigations and prevent miscarriages of justice.', 'Explore how your own mind works, and discover how the limitations of the human brain can lead to major miscarriages of justice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/forensic-psychology', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2340401.mp4', '2015-09-14', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/bd/09/regular_bd0923f5-3b95-4cf4-b0b9-297a9706d19d.jpg', 'Law', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:03'),
(143, 'Forensic Science and Criminal Justice', 'Learn how police use science in criminal investigations and its role in the criminal justice system with this free online course.', 'Over the past two decades, the criminal justice system has been dramatically affected by technological advances in scientific contributions to the law. The most influential developments have been in the area of DNA profiling, and its forensic applications for both identifying perpetrators and exonerating the innocent.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/forensic-crim-justice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2493477.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f7/63/regular_f76375a2-d1f5-4625-b706-1b5b5e3a67f9.jpg', 'Law', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leicester', '2015-11-04 00:02:04'),
(144, 'Exploring English: Shakespeare', 'Improve your English language skills by looking at the life and works of William Shakespeare and his enduring popularity.', 'This free online course will look at the life and works of William Shakespeare and take you from his Birthplace in Stratford-upon-Avon to the Globe Theatre in London, from where he secured his central place in English literature.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/explore-english-shakespeare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5517695.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/df/30/regular_df30152c-3fd2-4f96-a151-a39fcead4da3.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:02:05'),
(145, 'Start Writing Fiction', 'This hands-on course helps you to get started with your own fiction writing, focusing on the central skill of creating characters.', 'Start Writing Fiction focuses on a skill which is central to the writing of all stories and novels – creating characters.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/start-writing-fiction', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2648205.mp4', '2016-01-18', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/51/db/regular_51dbd3e2-84fa-4356-ad38-6b76738b6b03.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:06'),
(146, 'An Introduction to Screenwriting', 'This free online course explores the key concepts and fundamental principles involved in the process of screenwriting.', 'Screenplays form the starting point for most dramatic films, the essential work from which all other filmmaking flows. All of the tender romance, terrifying action and memorable lines begin at the screenwriter’s desk. This free online course will introduce you to the basic elements and key concepts behind a professional screenplay.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/screenwriting', '', '2016-02-29', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d2/70/regular_d270e847-b243-4ba7-ade2-a3b4a551e420.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:06'),
(147, 'World War 1: Changing Faces of Heroism', 'Learn how the war moved us away from traditional views of heroism and created new kinds of heroes and heroines.', 'Did World War 1 make heroism meaningless or was it the conflict that gave it the most meaning? We’ve designed this course in partnership with the BBC to help you explore, discuss and challenge the ways in which World War 1 heroism has been remembered. Our experts will take you through the changing British, French and German views of heroism and discuss important similarities and differences.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-heroism', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3053661.mp4', '2015-10-26', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/40/b5/regular_40b5ca70-dc9c-4f4f-8a13-c75f40ba818d.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:02:07'),
(148, 'Hans Christian Andersen’s Fairy Tales', 'Explore the fairy tale world of HC Andersen - the inspiration behind The Little Mermaid and Frozen - with this free online course.', 'This free online course will introduce you to some of Hans Christian Andersen’s most popular fairy tales, share the story of the writer himself, and discuss his cross-cultural importance today, as the inspiration behind many popular books and movies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/hans-christian-andersens-fairy-tales', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4397780.mp4', '2015-10-19', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/84/b6/regular_84b6a8b0-d253-4b29-982a-97e3f608c85c.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Hans Christian Andersen Centre', '2015-11-04 00:02:07'),
(149, 'Cultural Studies and Modern Languages: an Introduction', 'Explore the culture, language and national identity of eight countries through their books, images, slogans and monuments', 'Are you interested in other countries? Do you want to study and understand other cultures? This free online course will take you on a journey through a number of periods from the medieval to the modern day, from Russia to Europe and all the way to Latin America.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cultural-studies', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428991.mp4', '2015-10-12', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b5/c7/regular_b5c7c300-3189-4c96-ae66-597a6192c138.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bristol', '2015-11-04 00:02:08'),
(150, 'Start Writing Fiction', 'This hands-on course helps you to get started with your own fiction writing, focusing on the central skill of creating characters.', 'Start Writing Fiction focuses on a skill which is central to the writing of all stories and novels – creating characters.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/start-writing-fiction', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2648205.mp4', '2015-10-12', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2c/9b/regular_2c9b9500-3e8d-484c-9285-ada4803496de.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:09'),
(151, 'Shakespeare and his World', 'Together with the Shakespeare Birthplace Trust, Professor Jonathan Bate explores Shakespeare, his works and the world he lived in.', 'William Shakespeare is one of the most famous authors of all time. 2014 marked the 450th anniversary of his birth and his words have inspired and moved people from around the globe for centuries.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shakespeare-and-his-world', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1678642.mp4', '2015-10-05', 10, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1c/c9/regular_1cc90465-ed23-41be-b8f1-12c09e50cc81.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Warwick', '2015-11-04 00:02:10'),
(152, 'Corpus Linguistics: Method, Analysis, Interpretation', 'Offers practical introduction to the methodology of corpus linguistics for researchers in social sciences and humanities', 'The course aims to:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/corpus-linguistics', '', '2015-09-28', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/33/9f/regular_339ff074-1f50-4a77-a9d8-822cf939be13.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:10'),
(153, 'How to Read a Mind', 'How do we read and model fictional minds? Introducing cognitive poetics: the application of cognitive science to literary reading.', 'This course offers an introduction to what has come to be known as cognitive poetics. Taking our best current knowledge of how our minds and language work, this course takes you through key questions of literature and reading: why do we feel anything for fictional characters? Why do we get angry, moved, irritated, annoyed or sentimental about imaginary people in imagined worlds? Why do the lives of imaginary minds living in fictional bodies seem to matter so much to readers? The answers to these questions are surprising and empowering.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/how-to-read-a-mind', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/46/db/regular_46db5b59-369d-4663-a6e6-9f873f6117d1.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:11'),
(154, 'Literature of the English Country House', 'A journey through the literature of English country houses from the time of Thomas More to Oscar Wilde', 'On this free online course, you’ll investigate and discuss the role and representation of the English country house in literature, and learn how to build your own authoritative interpretation of these texts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/country-house-literature', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3883219.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2e/f9/regular_2ef9b9c8-0f63-4225-a153-7deabbbcbce8.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:02:12'),
(155, 'Much Ado about Nothing: in Performance', 'Explore how Much Ado about Nothing is performed and interpreted, from original stagings to the modern day, with this free course.', 'Shakespeare’s much loved play, Much Ado about Nothing, is read and studied all over the world. But it was written to be staged, and can only be fully appreciated and understood through performance.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/much-ado-about-nothing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2369693.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/48/a1/regular_48a12764-dbe4-4337-b76f-7ab4825706fd.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:13'),
(156, 'Reading Macondo: the Works of Gabriel García Márquez', 'Explore why the author of One Hundred Years of Solitude is one of the 20th century’s leading writers in this free online course', 'Gabriel García Márquez is a Colombian writer, who won the Literature Nobel Prize in 1982. He has been recognised as one of the world’s leading writers in the second half of the 20th century.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/macondo-gabriel-garcia-marquez', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3909272.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/69/98/regular_6998e295-7910-4180-9dfd-4fc18aff0940.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Los Andes', '2015-11-04 00:02:13'),
(157, 'Shakespeares Hamlet: Text, Performance and Culture', 'Experts from the Shakespeare Institute guide an exploration of the most famous play ever staged.', 'Hamlet is the most famous play ever written and the masterpiece of the most important writer in English, William Shakespeare. Its themes of mortality, madness and political succession have given it an enduring fascination - Hamlet has been translated into every major language and adapted for every new medium since it was written.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shakespeares-hamlet', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2196917.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e9/95/regular_e9953aa7-9c18-4279-8e84-6db2d24652e2.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:14'),
(158, 'William Wordsworth: Poetry, People and Place', 'Explore the influence of the Lake District on Wordsworth with this free online course, filmed at his home, Dove Cottage, Grasmere.', 'This free online course will explore the great poetry of William Wordsworth, with an emphasis on his writing process and the inspirational landscape of the Lake District. This course is presented in association with the Wordsworth Trust, Grasmere.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/william-wordsworth', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4010469.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2f/45/regular_2f45d08d-75e4-47c4-ad15-e1ca4329609f.jpg', 'Literature & Writing', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:14'),
(159, 'Sustainability, Society and You', 'Join us for an introduction to the major global issue of sustainability and discover how you can have a real impact on our future.', 'Sustainability is one of the big global issues of our time. It is crucial that we all play our part in protecting our world for current and future generations. This course provides you with the knowledge and skills to do this by investigating sustainability from multiple angles and exploring what small steps you can take to have a real impact upon all our futures.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/sustainability-society-and-you', '', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/de/regular_fade2622-3ae1-4ff2-83db-af529fc98553.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:15'),
(160, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Supply Chain Integrity', 'The challenges for food security in tracing and detecting food contamination whether it be by accident or as a result of fraud.', 'Humanity faces a considerable problem in maintaining and enhancing food supplies on a global basis, whilst improving our wellbeing in both the developing and developed world. Obesity and other growing problems related to dietary excess pose huge economic and health implications in the developed world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/global-food-crisis', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1987197.mp4', '2015-11-02', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/09/05/regular_09056b37-f7ba-43cb-92ff-bfffcbe948ae.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:16'),
(161, 'Our Changing Climate: Past, Present and Future', 'Find out more about the climate of the past and how climate change can present a number of risks and opportunities.', 'Since early humans first moved out of Africa, the world’s climate has had a continual impact on our history. Now, the climate itself is being shaped by civilisation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/our-changing-climate', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5039268.mp4', '2015-11-09', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/36/b7/regular_36b75c03-07cd-4c6f-b0d8-93118da74a70.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:16'),
(162, 'Our Hungry Planet: Agriculture, People and Food Security', 'Consider how the food we grow, buy, eat and throw away relates to the global issue of food security, with this free online course.', 'Food security is a complex, global issue, in which we all play a part. In this free online course, you’ll join experts from the School of Agriculture, Policy and Development at the University of Reading, to investigate our relationship with agriculture and your own food habits.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/our-hungry-planet', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2924674.mp4', '2015-11-09', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/69/e6/regular_69e69eca-9803-4fc0-be6c-e1581dce8582.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(163, 'Monitoring Climate from Space', 'Explore our planet from space and learn how Earth observation is used to monitor climate change, with this free online course.', 'It is increasingly essential for us to study climate change across the planet at the highest level of detail possible. But how can we achieve such a comprehensive worldwide view?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-from-space', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5573782.mp4', '2015-11-30', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/e7/regular_a4e7190e-bd62-49db-a067-c447a53b8709.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'European Space Agency', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(164, 'In the Night Sky: Orion', 'Explore the night sky, discover how stars formed and find out about exoplanets, all through the constellation of Orion.', 'From the basics of astronomy and stargazing, to the science behind the birth of a star, this four week course will change the way you see the night sky. You’ll examine one of the most famous constellations, Orion, who the Ancient Greeks believed was a huntsman placed among the stars by Zeus himself.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/orion', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5334054.mp4', '2016-01-04', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ae/f3/regular_aef30283-74eb-43e5-aac8-b25365494c62.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:17'),
(165, 'Environmental Humanities: Remaking Nature', 'Learn how the new Environmental Humanities field is shaping how we understand environmental issues, with this free online course.', 'In Environmental Humanities: Remaking Nature, you’ll get a broad overview of an emerging area of interdisciplinary research that reframes contemporary environmental challenges using approaches from philosophy, literature, language, history, anthropology, cultural studies and the arts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/remaking-nature', '', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/f0/regular_faf0e28b-3637-46ef-b2db-0b68ff609a67.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:02:18'),
(166, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Sustainable Agrifood Systems', 'This course looks at food insecurity and the challenges to be overcome in order to maintain healthy and sustainable food supplies.', 'This is the second course in a two-part series by Queen’s University Belfast looking at issues concerning the maintenance and enhancement of global food supplies, whilst improving human wellbeing in the developed and developing world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/agrifood', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2089358.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/58/5f/regular_585f12a2-9455-4cf3-b969-3e04243a1934.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:18'),
(167, 'Energy: Thermodynamics in Everyday Life', 'Understand the laws of thermodynamics – and how they govern how we use and lose energy everyday – in this free online course.', 'Energy is essential to life at many levels and its transformation from one form to another – whether in the cells of our bodies or the machines that enable modern society – is governed by the laws of thermodynamics.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5569610.mp4', '2016-02-01', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/71/62/regular_7162e433-558b-47e2-b263-195f8be0f45b.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'no', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:02:19'),
(168, 'Exploring Possible Futures: Modeling in Environmental and Energy Economics', 'Look to the future, learning how to develop and use models in environmental and energy economics, with this free online course.', 'What will efficient cities look like in future? How do humans contribute to climate change? Is a completely renewable energy supply possible? To explore our possible futures, we need models.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/exploring-possible-futures', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4639630.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/db/54/regular_db545c7a-45a5-4b94-af1c-be78e2c85027.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Basel', '2015-11-04 00:02:20'),
(169, 'Moons', 'Explore the many moons of our Solar System. Find out what makes them special. Should we send humans to our Moon again?', 'There are lots of moons in our Solar System. The Earth is the only planet with just a single moon. Some moons are bigger than ours; many are much smaller. There are even tiny moons orbiting some of the asteroids. Some have ongoing volcanic eruptions; others are dead, heavily cratered lumps. One has rivers and lakes of liquid methane. Our own Moon has resources that could help open the Solar System for future exploration. A small handful of moons have conditions below their surfaces where primitive life might exist.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/moons', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2096693.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/45/58/regular_45589460-fec1-4b42-96d9-ecd89c0a4e13.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:20'),
(170, 'Solving the Energy Puzzle: A Multidisciplinary Approach to Energy Transition', 'Learn how to analyse energy transition cases from technological, legal, economics, spatial, and social perspectives.', 'Since the discovery of fire, mankind has used various energy sources to aid our development. The energy system has been continually changing, as the economy and technology progress.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/energy-transition', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4509115.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/90/d2/regular_90d29d5a-20c5-42c7-9b40-229f2233779a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:02:21'),
(171, 'Causes of Climate Change', 'Understand the physical processes behind climate variations in the past, present and future, with this free online course', 'This free online course provides the basis for understanding the underlying physical processes governing climate variations in the past, present and future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/causes-of-climate-change', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4147256.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a1/84/regular_a184ac4b-f773-4ba7-87bb-fb9a23b1792c.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bergen', '2015-11-04 00:02:22'),
(172, 'Climate Change: Challenges and Solutions', 'This course aims to explain the science of climate change, the risks it poses and the solutions available to reduce those risks.', 'The course is aimed at the level of students entering university, and seeks to provide an inter-disciplinary introduction to what is a broad field. It engages a number of experts from the University of Exeter and a number of partner organisations.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-change-challenges-and-solutions', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2136990.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/cb/71/regular_cb71114d-b163-4486-908d-20dadfde623e.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Exeter', '2015-11-04 00:02:23'),
(173, 'Elements of Renewable Energy', 'Learn how sustainable energy from the Greek elements – Earth, Air, Fire and Water – can replace fossil fuels and nuclear power.', 'In recent decades there’s been increasing global concern about the sustainability of our use of fossil fuels and nuclear power, which has led to increased interest in more sustainable renewable energy sources.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/elements-renewable-energies', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0e/e1/regular_0ee1deec-38ac-46df-82a5-4d4b0f0bad4c.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:23'),
(174, 'Environmental Justice', 'Understand how environmental change affects people, and how we can work together for justice in environmental management.', 'The world faces challenging environmental problems. They are challenging because different people typically contribute differently to environmental change, and because its effects will be felt differently by different people in different places.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/environmental-justice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428282.mp4', '0000-00-00', 10, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b2/83/regular_b283c88b-3644-499d-b965-cef376be50cd.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:24'),
(175, 'Exploring Our Oceans', 'Explore the half of our world covered by deep ocean, and how our lives affect the hidden face of our planet.', 'The first astronauts to leave the Earth’s orbit saw our “blue planet” for the first time. But what lies in the half of our world covered by water more than two miles deep? How are our everyday lives connected to the ocean depths, and what challenges and opportunities does this previously hidden realm hold for our future?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/exploring-our-oceans', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d9/e6/regular_d9e61125-ca2d-4240-abba-751ca981345f.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:25'),
(176, 'Fairness and Nature: When Worlds Collide', 'Making decisions about managing natural resources can be difficult; this course explores why fairness needs to be part of policy.', 'This course is about making difficult decisions on the management of natural resources. Different people place different values on nature. For example, some see it as something we should conserve for future generations, others as a resource of financial value to be exploited. Policies about managing nature should be economically and environmentally sound, but they also need to be formulated with social fairness if they are to be sustainable. Inevitably, when there are so many different values, conflicts occur and worlds collide.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/fairness-and-nature', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1345241.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/7b/ee/regular_7beee768-9454-46b4-b4c7-9ec567b8165d.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:02:25'),
(177, 'Global Food Security: Addressing the Challenge', 'How will we feed an extra two billion people by the middle of this century?', 'In this course, we introduce the issue of food security and explore some of the different ways in which it has been described both in research and in practice and consider key concerns for the future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/food-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2550056.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/74/1a/regular_741a7f06-e579-4f08-8bc0-a2efb60c4a7a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:26'),
(178, 'Introduction to Ecosystems', 'Gain an understanding of the natural world, how the web of life works, with illustrations from around the world.', 'If we don’t grasp why ecosystems function, it becomes harder to determine possible reasons for when they don’t, and makes it difficult to identify possible environmental threats to humans. In this course you will discover how organisms are linked together by complex interrelationships, how such links are studied and how the physical properties of a particular habitat interact with the organisms that inhabit it. Using case studies, you will come to learn how knowledge of ecosystems leads to understanding of their individual importance, and how they can be preserved.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ecosystems', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2389989.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/2e/regular_ef2e01b3-f7a4-4358-8d81-53bbf347063a.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:27'),
(179, 'Make an Impact: Sustainability for Professionals', 'Find out how to integrate a sustainable development strategy into your company with this free online course', 'This free online course will cover the basic definitions and history of sustainable development and sustainability in business - from a niche interest to the present day.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/sustainability-for-professionals', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1413352.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/31/d5/regular_31d5e65d-bb75-4eb9-978b-7f882a80e862.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bath', '2015-11-04 00:02:27'),
(180, 'Shale Gas and Fracking: the Politics and Science', 'Hear from all sides of the fracking debate with this free online course. Understand what shale gas is and why it divides opinion.', 'Shale gas is seen by many as a cheap, clean and plentiful source of energy; a low-carbon ‘game changer’ helping us meet the world’s rapidly growing demands for energy and offering greater energy security. Its rapid rise has not been without controversy, however. Earth tremors, surface and groundwater contamination, and the effects of fracking on human and animal health are all high profile concerns.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shale-gas', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2317839.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/3c/ac/regular_3caca682-b4ac-4240-8621-d58a9c0ac586.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:28'),
(181, 'Shipwrecks and Submerged Worlds: Maritime Archaeology', 'Learn how maritime archaeology investigates our changing relationship with the oceans and seas, from 2.5m years ago until today', 'People have explored and depended on the oceans of our planet for millennia. During that time the geography of our world has changed radically as coastal regions have flooded and islands have risen up, or been lost beneath the waves. With 70% of the world’s surface covered by water, an unparalleled, yet largely untouched record of human life has been left beneath the sea for us to discover, from our earliest ancestors right through to present day. Over the length of this Shipwrecks and Submerged Worlds course we will learn about maritime archaeology together - exploring underwater landscapes from the ancient Mediterranean to the prehistoric North Sea, and consider Shipwrecks from the Indian Ocean to the Pacific coast of the Americas.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shipwrecks', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3259029.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/87/fc/regular_87fc6f31-2a02-4a14-974f-df1d9f62e701.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:28'),
(182, 'Soils: Introducing the World Beneath Our Feet', 'Learn about soils, the variety of life they contain and how humans impact this fragile system, with this free online course.', 'Soils are a vital part of our planet’s functioning, but all too often we take soils for granted. In this free online course, we introduce you to soils and explore the world beneath our feet.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/soils', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3693052.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/e6/regular_42e6e9b4-5a4f-43b4-bd68-ecd46f957777.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:02:29'),
(183, 'The Science of Nuclear Energy', 'Discover the science behind nuclear energy and its role in energy provision in the past, present and future.', 'With the need to reduce carbon emissions around the world, the way we generate our power has to change and nuclear energy is back on the political agenda. But do you know your fission from your fusion? Would you like the knowledge to make an informed decision?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-nuclear-energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3933347.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2c/51/regular_2c51f90d-2504-47bb-8816-c834b4e29b99.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:30'),
(184, 'Water for Liveable and Resilient Cities', 'Learn how water can be used in the planning of cities to improve liveability in the face of climate change and population growth.', 'Water plays a central role in almost every aspect of our urban environment and quality of life in our cities. Alarmingly, the combined impacts of rapid population growth and climate change are now posing a severe threat to the liveability and resilience of our cities.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/liveable-cities', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2131245.mp4', '0000-00-00', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/5a/c0/regular_5ac04df6-27c0-4468-b0d1-96d57f11a7f1.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:02:30'),
(185, 'What Works: Promising Practices in International Development', 'Explore promising strategies in international aid related to agriculture, public health, governance, and poverty reduction.', 'The history of international development is a complicated mixture of hopeful altruism and difficult reality. The media often paint development aid as wasteful spending, leaving the public wondering if any intervention can ever work. Yet can the case be made for a more optimistic outlook on international development?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/what-works', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2402606.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/17/fc/regular_17fc7ab1-9d5f-4463-be05-efedf4120f31.jpg', 'Environment & Biology', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Oslo', '2015-11-04 00:02:31'),
(186, 'The Internet of Things', 'Learn how IoT works, and how to create a successful product or company using it, with this free online course.', 'Entrepreneurs love it, large corporations love it, universities and now even governments love it – welcome to the exciting and emerging world of the Internet of Things (IoT).', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/internet-of-things', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4611259.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8e/44/regular_8e442a5c-4cee-4fd3-8f8f-ed04df2789cd.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Kings College London', '2015-11-04 00:02:34'),
(187, 'Bioprinting: 3D Printing Body Parts', 'Discover how biomaterials and 3D printing collide, to create revolutionary, bioprinted body parts, with this free online course.', 'You may be aware of 3D printing or have seen low-cost 3D printers, which can create plastic toys, replicas and objects of your own design. But did you know that 3D printing is also enabling life-saving and transforming medical procedures, which were unthinkable a few years ago?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/bioprinting', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4894894.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e6/3f/regular_e63f6908-c6bc-4bc2-9059-d18064cac286.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Australian Institute for Innovative Materials, University of Wollongong ', '2015-11-04 00:02:34'),
(188, 'Web Science: How the Web Is Changing the World', 'Explore how the web has changed our world and what the future might hold, with this free online course introducing Web Science.', 'You may already be an avid user of the Web, but this introduction to Web Science will help you better understand it as both a social and technical system - a global information infrastructure, built from the interactions of people and technologies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/web-science', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5294960.mp4', '2015-11-30', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/91/42/regular_914240b3-f131-47cb-90a5-be0a430aa70e.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:35'),
(189, 'Social Media in Healthcare: Opportunities and Challenges', 'Understand how social media is used in healthcare, to improve communication and information sharing, with this free online course.', 'Social media has emerged as a new channel for both seeking information, and for creating and exchanging user-generated content among peers.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/social-media-in-healthcare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5435393.mp4', '2015-11-30', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e4/96/regular_e4961de7-feb1-455e-8114-c9471a3027f9.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Taipei Medical University', '2015-11-04 00:02:36'),
(190, 'Introduction to Cyber Security', 'Our lives depend on online services. Gain essential cyber security knowledge and skills, to help protect your digital life.', 'We shop online. We work online. We play online. We live online. As our lives increasingly depend on digital services, the need to protect our information from being maliciously disrupted or misused is really important.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/introduction-to-cyber-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3488942.mp4', '2016-01-04', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e0/bc/regular_e0bc186c-7d75-445e-acce-21656f172c47.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:37'),
(191, 'Get Started with Online Learning', 'This free online course will explain how you can study online without putting the rest of your life on hold.', 'The internet is playing a bigger role in our lives, as we buy our groceries, manage our finances, share social experiences and otherwise live our lives online. But how many of us have considered studying online?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/online-learning', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4763094.mp4', '2016-01-04', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ce/19/regular_ce19db60-1224-442e-9df3-e38913259994.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:38'),
(192, 'Transmedia Storytelling', 'Learn how to tell compelling stories across multiple platforms, like books, films, games and TV, with this free online course.', 'Stories are increasingly told across a variety of formats, such as books, comics, events, films, games and TV programmes - a trend known as transmedia storytelling or multiplatform storytelling.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/transmedia-storytelling', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5451882.mp4', '2016-01-18', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/40/a7/regular_40a7200a-b643-4bea-b7e4-5e670de9533c.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Sungkyunkwan University (SKKU) ', '2015-11-04 00:02:38'),
(193, 'Digital Leadership: Creating Value Through Technology', 'Digital technologies are changing extraordinarily quickly. This four-week course will introduce you to the new digital landscape.', 'In this course you will learn how to:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/digital-leadership', '', '2016-02-08', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b8/88/regular_b888ab0c-c46e-4a35-afa8-9b946a74cfa0.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:39'),
(194, 'Learn to Code for Data Analysis', 'Software and data make the world go round. Learn programming, to analyse and visualise open data, with this free online course.', 'This hands-on course will teach you how to write your own computer programs, one line of code at a time. You’ll learn how to access open data, clean it and analyse it and to produce visualisations. You will also learn how to write up and share your analyses, privately or publicly.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/learn-to-code', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4731244.mp4', '2015-10-26', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1d/79/regular_1d7976bd-1f5e-4c90-a72a-233fe6ce7b49.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:40'),
(195, 'Digital Marketing: Challenges and Insights', 'Explore the latest trends in digital marketing. Get beneath the hype. What are the implications? How will you respond?', 'This short course introduces you to exciting new concepts and applications of digital marketing. It takes an informal “story telling” approach, encouraging you to share your own stories as consumers and/or marketers for the benefit of the learner group as a whole.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/digital-marketing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1756128.mp4', '2015-10-19', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d2/75/regular_d27599ca-eb59-4fe1-a538-0b1ceffd3e10.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:02:40'),
(196, 'Begin Programming: Build Your First Mobile Game', 'Learn basic Java programming by developing a simple mobile game that you can run on your computer, Android phone, or tablet.', 'Programming is everywhere: in dishwashers, cars and even space shuttles. This course will help you to understand how programs work and guide you through creating your own computer program – a mobile game.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/begin-programming', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4251365.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c9/9c/regular_c99cbca8-6bf5-44f2-9bb9-17c21efc8e72.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:41'),
(197, 'Introduction to Cyber Security', 'Our lives depend on online services. Gain essential cyber security knowledge and skills, to help protect your digital life.', 'We shop online. We work online. We play online. We live online. As our lives increasingly depend on digital services, the need to protect our information from being maliciously disrupted or misused is really important.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/introduction-to-cyber-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3488942.mp4', '2015-10-05', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/af/ef/regular_afef979f-493c-461a-bfd9-97d30d3cb1eb.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:41'),
(198, 'Begin Robotics', 'Explore the history, anatomy and intelligence of robots with this free online course. Test drive robots using exciting simulations', 'Robots today are roving Mars, collecting data in dangerous environments, hoovering our floors, lifting patients in hospital, building cars and entertaining us in films. And, if you share Bill Gates and Stephen Hawking’s world view, the super intelligent ones may one day bring about the end of the human race.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/begin-robotics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3697356.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/82/ce/regular_82ce6165-30a4-440e-ad57-a7e8f9e77220.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:02:42'),
(199, 'Big Data: Measuring and Predicting Human Behaviour', 'Join us to explore how the vast amounts of data generated today can help us understand and even predict how humans behave.', 'We increasingly rely on networked computer systems and smart cards to support our everyday activities, and everything we do generates data – whether buying bread at the supermarket, taking a ride on public transport, or calling a friend for a chat.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/big-data', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2705064.mp4', '0000-00-00', 9, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a7/57/regular_a7574c1e-db70-49e1-9060-9ba19d00f6f2.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Warwick', '2015-11-04 00:02:43');
INSERT INTO `course_data` (`id`, `title`, `short_desc`, `long_desc`, `course_link`, `video_link`, `start_date`, `course_length`, `course_image`, `category`, `site`, `course_fee`, `language`, `certificate`, `university`, `time_scraped`) VALUES
(200, 'Childhood in the Digital Age', 'Delve into the lives of children and discuss the potential benefits and limitations of technology in their lives.', 'Are you a technology optimist or a technology pessimist?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/childhood-in-the-digital-age', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4530272.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/14/f8/regular_14f8f7d0-c6ec-4d94-a99c-acff489aeb38.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:44'),
(201, 'Community Journalism: Digital and Social Media', 'Gain practical skills and insights into hyperlocal journalism, and use digital and social media to create your own news website.', 'Community journalism is a growing area of interest for professional journalists, academics and the wider public. The decline of local newspapers and radio stations, coupled with the low cost of publishing online, means there are more community journalism and hyperlocal websites being launched everyday.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/community-journalism', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2358128.mp4', '0000-00-00', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d3/54/regular_d3548457-a375-456b-8ecc-7533e9050fca.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Cardiff University', '2015-11-04 00:02:46'),
(202, 'Creative Coding', 'Use computer programming as a creative discipline to generate sounds, images, animations and more, with this free online course.', 'Learning to program is no longer just for computer specialists and software developers. People from many different backgrounds now want to understand the basics of programming, because it’s both fun and an increasingly valuable skill.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/creative-coding', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1569932.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8e/98/regular_8e98b3b7-689e-457a-95ac-c1523d7d5242.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:02:47'),
(203, 'Digital Storytelling: Filmmaking for the Web', 'Combine theory and practice to tell powerful stories through film online. Unleash your potential in this free online course.', 'The University of Birmingham, the BBC Academy and Creative Skillset have combined forces, to create this four-week, free online course.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/digital-storytelling', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4315019.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/9a/b5/regular_9ab51686-7c98-4e16-ba4b-d59af4d71ce1.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:48'),
(204, 'Teaching Computing', 'A free online course for primary and secondary school teachers who are tackling the Computing curriculum in England.', 'This free online course aims to help teachers in primary schools and at Key Stage 3, who are delivering the Computing curriculum, which was introduced to schools in England in September 2014.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/teaching-computing', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d2/c5/regular_d2c51ff2-0c67-41aa-ab9c-10e9c1835f4e.jpg', 'Programming & IT', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:49'),
(205, 'Sustainability, Society and You', 'Join us for an introduction to the major global issue of sustainability and discover how you can have a real impact on our future.', 'Sustainability is one of the big global issues of our time. It is crucial that we all play our part in protecting our world for current and future generations. This course provides you with the knowledge and skills to do this by investigating sustainability from multiple angles and exploring what small steps you can take to have a real impact upon all our futures.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/sustainability-society-and-you', '', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/de/regular_fade2622-3ae1-4ff2-83db-af529fc98553.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:50'),
(206, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Supply Chain Integrity', 'The challenges for food security in tracing and detecting food contamination whether it be by accident or as a result of fraud.', 'Humanity faces a considerable problem in maintaining and enhancing food supplies on a global basis, whilst improving our wellbeing in both the developing and developed world. Obesity and other growing problems related to dietary excess pose huge economic and health implications in the developed world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/global-food-crisis', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1987197.mp4', '2015-11-02', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/09/05/regular_09056b37-f7ba-43cb-92ff-bfffcbe948ae.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:51'),
(207, 'Tackling the Global Food Crisis: Sustainable Agrifood Systems', 'This course looks at food insecurity and the challenges to be overcome in order to maintain healthy and sustainable food supplies.', 'This is the second course in a two-part series by Queen’s University Belfast looking at issues concerning the maintenance and enhancement of global food supplies, whilst improving human wellbeing in the developed and developing world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/agrifood', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2089358.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/58/5f/regular_585f12a2-9455-4cf3-b969-3e04243a1934.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:02:52'),
(208, 'Africa: Sustainable Development for All?', 'Learn what progress Africa has made towards inclusive development and consider challenges post-2015 in this free online course.', 'Africa as a continent is rich in natural resources and minerals and has increasing rates of wealth in some countries. The course will explore why there continues to be many sub-Saharan African countries which perform poorly on development indicators for reducing poverty, hunger and unemployment and improving maternal health and access to quality reproductive health services.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/africa-sustainable-development', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3920380.mp4', '2016-01-25', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/32/6a/regular_326a81ea-0cc3-4bde-9ddf-a78ccbeea382.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Aberdeen', '2015-11-04 00:02:52'),
(209, 'Understanding Public Financial Management: How Is Your Money Spent?', 'How do governments acquire and spend public money? Take a fresh look at public financial management with this free online course.', 'What went wrong in Greece’s handling of its public debt? How does a city government like Detroit go from prosperity to bankruptcy? And how could the looting, theft and corruption in Malawi’s “cashgate” have been avoided?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/public-financial-management', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5441427.mp4', '2016-01-25', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/12/regular_ef1250d1-3017-48da-b50d-d032a15e5029.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'SOAS, University of London', '2015-11-04 00:02:53'),
(210, 'Military Ethics: An Introduction', 'We explore the ethical responsibilities that weigh on military professionals, who are ‘managers of violence’.', 'Military professionals are unusual in having the use of lethal force as a central, defining feature of their role, and unique in the level of force that they are authorized to use. This fact places a considerable ethical weight on military practitioners as well as the civilian decision-makers who authorize military missions.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/military-ethics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5387660.mp4', '2016-02-29', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f2/02/regular_f2020743-f023-4d3a-bac1-fafa5907d58f.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:02:53'),
(211, 'Scotland and Wales Vote 2016: Understanding the Devolved Elections', 'This course wil examine the issues, ideas and institutions involved in the Scottish Parliament and Welsh Assembly elections.', '2016 is an exciting year for elections in the United Kingdom. Towards the end of the year we might have a referendum on the UK’s EU membership, but we definitely know that there will be elections to the Scottish Parliament and Welsh Assembly in May. Both of these institutions have a significant impact on people’s lives in Scotland and Wales: they control big public policy issues like health, education and transport.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/scottish-welsh-elections16', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5435747.mp4', '2016-04-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b5/25/regular_b525867d-1a7e-4f70-bda6-760e3fc5a516.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Edinburgh', '2015-11-04 00:02:54'),
(212, 'Crime, Justice and Society', 'Explore the role of the state and criminal justice interventions in producing safe and just societies', 'Crime and criminal justice are vast and fascinating issues that highlight the complexity of defining and solving social problems.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/crime-justice-society', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4928778.mp4', '2015-10-12', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/08/regular_a4085e9b-8156-4c36-b135-378813639661.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:02:55'),
(213, 'Religion and Conflict', 'Understand and analyze the role of religion in conflicts and peacebuilding in present-day societies, with this free online course.', 'Many conflicts in the world today are framed in terms of religion, but there is much discussion and confusion concerning the precise role religion plays in these conflicts. According to some, conflict and violence are inherent to religion. Others claim that religion is only the guise under which social, economic or political conflicts are fought out. The first step to solving religiously framed conflicts is understanding the role of religion in them, and that is what this free online course is about.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/religion-and-conflict', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3022180.mp4', '2015-10-05', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d7/ef/regular_d7ef63d4-5ee9-409f-9b5f-be27016bc9eb.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:02:56'),
(214, 'Causes of War', 'What causes armed conflict in the world today? Examine current thinking on this critical question with this free online course.', 'This free online course will introduce you to current thinking on the causes of armed conflict in the world today. It looks at a range of modern and historical conflicts and draws on a variety of theories and approaches. It will appeal to anyone with an interest in world affairs.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/causes-of-war', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2641095.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a0/69/regular_a069122d-914e-4328-8fcd-704562070123.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Kings College London', '2015-11-04 00:02:56'),
(215, 'Challenging Wealth and Income Inequality', 'Explore the concerns about rising generational and economic inequality in developed countries, with this free online course.', 'From religious leaders to heads of state, everyone is talking about economic inequality. What form can such inequality take in different countries? What impact does it have on society? And why should it matter to you?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/inequalities-in-personal-finance', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2763907.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c6/8f/regular_c68fc17f-f2b2-4b0d-b9d3-2ef55bb681d9.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:02:57'),
(216, 'Cooperation in the Contemporary World: Unlocking International Politics', 'Why do we cooperate? How can we achieve more lasting cooperation? This course explores the puzzle in international politics today.', 'As world leaders seek to find a solution to crises in Syria and Ukraine; economists try to reinvigorate stalling global financial markets; and a range of actors gather to find a consensus on climate change, there has never been a better time to understand the puzzle of cooperation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cooperation-in-the-contemporary-world', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4149980.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/1c/c6/regular_1cc604f0-636e-425d-80a9-34ae7880a164.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:02:58'),
(217, 'Environmental Justice', 'Understand how environmental change affects people, and how we can work together for justice in environmental management.', 'The world faces challenging environmental problems. They are challenging because different people typically contribute differently to environmental change, and because its effects will be felt differently by different people in different places.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/environmental-justice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428282.mp4', '0000-00-00', 10, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b2/83/regular_b283c88b-3644-499d-b965-cef376be50cd.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:02:58'),
(218, 'From State Control to Remote Control: Warfare in the 21st Century', 'Explore the impact and ethics of using drones, special ops units and private security firms, with this free online course.', 'States are increasingly using remote control methods, such as drones, private military companies and special operations units, to engage in activities that were traditionally performed by their conventional armed forces.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/remote-control-warfare', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2662019.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d8/17/regular_d817f134-8706-4769-a704-12400797fbfc.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bath', '2015-11-04 00:02:59'),
(219, 'Global Food Security: Addressing the Challenge', 'How will we feed an extra two billion people by the middle of this century?', 'In this course, we introduce the issue of food security and explore some of the different ways in which it has been described both in research and in practice and consider key concerns for the future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/food-security', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2550056.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/74/1a/regular_741a7f06-e579-4f08-8bc0-a2efb60c4a7a.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:03:00'),
(220, 'Identity, Conflict and Public Space', 'Explore how people use public spaces around the world to protest and express their identity, with this free online course.', 'In ethnic and political conflicts around the world, public spaces are used by diverse groups of people, to express their identity and protest about their beliefs:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/identity-conflict-and-public-space', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1401981.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/14/19/regular_141937f4-9e01-430f-b96d-d16c9868e28c.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Queens University Belfast', '2015-11-04 00:03:00'),
(221, 'Lips and Teeth: Korea and China in Modern Times', 'Explore the historical evolution of China and the Korean Peninsula and discover the implications for today.', 'As countries across Asia - and the globe - wrestle with the impact of China’s rise, nowhere are the opportunities and threats of a wealthy and powerful China felt more keenly than next door, on the Korean Peninsula.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/korea-and-china', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2419110.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/60/5e/regular_605e0239-009a-451d-aa14-57eee58b3259.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Yonsei University', '2015-11-04 00:03:01'),
(222, 'Modern Korean History: Liberation, War and Nuclear Ambitions', 'Explore the unique and untold history of North and South Korea - from 1945 to the present - with this free online course.', 'The contemporary history of the Korean peninsula has been a tumultuous tale of decolonization, war and rapid economic development. Both North and South Korea has had an immense impact on the world stage and today many wonder why this region of East Asia appears so frequently in the international news.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/modern-korean-history', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2372067.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ff/51/regular_ff5143af-a195-45ae-9e42-aff3857da80e.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Yonsei University', '2015-11-04 00:03:02'),
(223, 'Propaganda and Ideology in Everyday Life', 'Find out how propaganda is used to instil political ideologies and its impact on our daily lives, with this free online course.', 'This free online course explores the building blocks of our political views: freedom, community, place, justice and choice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/propaganda', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2801553.mp4', '0000-00-00', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/23/regular_ef2351cc-cde8-4ed0-9801-4bfc380e0930.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:03:03'),
(224, 'Shale Gas and Fracking: the Politics and Science', 'Hear from all sides of the fracking debate with this free online course. Understand what shale gas is and why it divides opinion.', 'Shale gas is seen by many as a cheap, clean and plentiful source of energy; a low-carbon ‘game changer’ helping us meet the world’s rapidly growing demands for energy and offering greater energy security. Its rapid rise has not been without controversy, however. Earth tremors, surface and groundwater contamination, and the effects of fracking on human and animal health are all high profile concerns.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/shale-gas', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2317839.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/3c/ac/regular_3caca682-b4ac-4240-8621-d58a9c0ac586.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Nottingham', '2015-11-04 00:03:03'),
(225, 'Superpowers of the Ancient World: the Near East', 'Experience the world’s first international age, 3,500 years ago in the ancient Near East, with this free online course.', 'Over four weeks, this free online course explores four ancient Near-Eastern cultures and how they interacted with each other 3,500 years ago.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/superpowers-near-east', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4115194.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/33/8c/regular_338c724e-a5c0-4318-a826-0d253678383d.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:03:04'),
(226, 'The Lottery of Birth', 'Birth is a lottery. Where, when and to whom you are born and the society into which you are born will influence your life chances.', 'This free online course will look at both the big picture of the ‘lottery of birth’ and the smaller, human stories. You will examine the inequalities of birth, particularly being born rich or poor and being born female or male.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/lottery-of-birth', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/04/33/regular_04332853-0e02-4bcb-ba23-c4a2275ac789.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:05'),
(227, 'What Works: Promising Practices in International Development', 'Explore promising strategies in international aid related to agriculture, public health, governance, and poverty reduction.', 'The history of international development is a complicated mixture of hopeful altruism and difficult reality. The media often paint development aid as wasteful spending, leaving the public wondering if any intervention can ever work. Yet can the case be made for a more optimistic outlook on international development?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/what-works', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2402606.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/17/fc/regular_17fc7ab1-9d5f-4463-be05-efedf4120f31.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Oslo', '2015-11-04 00:03:05'),
(228, 'World War 1: Paris 1919 - A New World Order?', 'This course reassesses the legacy of the Paris Peace Conference (1919) and how it sought to create a new world order.', 'The Paris Peace Conference of 1919 ended a Great War, but it also designed the post-war future. In 1919, world leaders assembled in Paris redrew the map of the world, partitioned and created countries, and ushered in a new era of international relations. The naivety of the peace-makers of 1919 has been justly criticised. However, in setting up a permanent ‘world organisation’, the League of Nations, they changed the management of world affairs forever.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ww1-new-world-order', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2196589.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/23/7e/regular_237e6c99-3f52-4853-96e0-bafa0e3dfdd1.jpg', '', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Glasgow', '2015-11-04 00:03:05'),
(229, 'Improving Your Image: Dental Photography in Practice', 'Learn how to achieve consistent and excellent results in all aspects of dental photography with this free online course.', 'This free course will cover all aspects of the use of digital photography in dental practice: intra-oral, extra-oral, and portraits. Participants will be taken through photography, from the basics of choosing correct equipment and setting it up, to optimum settings, techniques for consistent imaging and the safe storage of images.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dental-photography-in-practice', '', '2015-11-02', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ab/4f/regular_ab4fe1b5-2203-48de-85fa-ad0b5275d473.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:03:07'),
(230, 'Cracking Mechanics: Further Maths for Engineers', 'Practise the maths, learn the physics, and find out how engineers use both to solve real world problems.', 'The aim of this free online course is to introduce you to some of the physics and maths that engineers find useful. The content comprises: parts of A-level maths and further maths (mechanics); the physical laws which this maths is used to model; and examples of how these skills are employed in mechanical, aerospace, civil, environmental, materials and electrical engineering.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cracking-mechanics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3042441.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/45/40/regular_454057f3-177d-40d1-a5e3-e549dda27a18.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bristol', '2015-11-04 00:03:08'),
(231, 'Why Do We Age? The Molecular Mechanisms of Ageing', 'Why do we age? Is there a limit to human lifespan? Can we prolong our lives? Find out with this free online course.', 'The “why” and “how” of ageing has puzzled mankind ever since it questioned its place in the universe. However, it was only after infectious diseases became more controlled and reliable food supplies became generally available, that the rapid increase of the average lifespan made science turn its attention to study longevity and ageing.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ageing', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3155756.mp4', '2015-11-02', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/2a/regular_422a2468-5da5-4fe4-85d9-bd78671b980c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:03:10'),
(232, 'Improving Healthcare Through Clinical Research', 'Find out how medical treatments are discovered, tested and evaluated, to improve healthcare for all, on this free online course.', 'Everything we do in healthcare - every tablet that’s prescribed, every treatment that’s given and every test that’s performed - has to be first discovered and then thoroughly evaluated before it can be put into practice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/clinical-research', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5394540.mp4', '2015-11-02', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a8/e8/regular_a8e878c7-6b58-4e07-9895-ae0403ee7540.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:11'),
(233, 'Electrify: An Introduction to Electrical and Electronic Engineering', 'How do we move things with electricity? How do the parts inside your computer work? Find out in Electrify.', 'Engineering is all about using science to make the world a better place and touches our everyday lives; the device you’re reading this on wouldn’t exist if it wasn’t for electrical and electronic engineers!', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/electrify', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1613333.mp4', '2015-11-09', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/82/8d/regular_828d95f9-e363-408a-a9b8-b14f48464d8e.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:03:12'),
(234, 'Our Changing Climate: Past, Present and Future', 'Find out more about the climate of the past and how climate change can present a number of risks and opportunities.', 'Since early humans first moved out of Africa, the world’s climate has had a continual impact on our history. Now, the climate itself is being shaped by civilisation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/our-changing-climate', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5039268.mp4', '2015-11-09', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/36/b7/regular_36b75c03-07cd-4c6f-b0d8-93118da74a70.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:03:14'),
(235, 'Real World Calculus: How Maths Drives Formula One and Launches Angry Birds', 'Understand how maths, such as differentiation and integration, is applied in everyday life with this free online calculus course.', 'Mathematics is at the heart of many aspects of modern life. Whether playing a game on your mobile phone, watching a Grand Prix or waking up to sunlight in the morning, maths (and more precisely, calculus) is behind the scenes.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/real-world-calculus', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2633166.mp4', '2015-11-09', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fe/04/regular_fe0442a4-9383-490b-9628-e407def4708c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leicester', '2015-11-04 00:03:15'),
(236, 'Basic Science: Understanding Numbers', 'This course explains how you can use numbers to describe the natural world and make sense of everything from atoms to oceans.', 'This practical, hands-on course will help you to start thinking like a scientist, by using numbers to describe and understand the natural world.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/understanding-numbers', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3030512.mp4', '2015-11-23', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c2/57/regular_c2574880-125e-464d-a23c-ee56d772dc9c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:16'),
(237, 'Web Science: How the Web Is Changing the World', 'Explore how the web has changed our world and what the future might hold, with this free online course introducing Web Science.', 'You may already be an avid user of the Web, but this introduction to Web Science will help you better understand it as both a social and technical system - a global information infrastructure, built from the interactions of people and technologies.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/web-science', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5294960.mp4', '2015-11-30', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/91/42/regular_914240b3-f131-47cb-90a5-be0a430aa70e.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:03:17'),
(238, 'Monitoring Climate from Space', 'Explore our planet from space and learn how Earth observation is used to monitor climate change, with this free online course.', 'It is increasingly essential for us to study climate change across the planet at the highest level of detail possible. But how can we achieve such a comprehensive worldwide view?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-from-space', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5573782.mp4', '2015-11-30', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/e7/regular_a4e7190e-bd62-49db-a067-c447a53b8709.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'European Space Agency', '2015-11-04 00:03:18'),
(239, 'In the Night Sky: Orion', 'Explore the night sky, discover how stars formed and find out about exoplanets, all through the constellation of Orion.', 'From the basics of astronomy and stargazing, to the science behind the birth of a star, this four week course will change the way you see the night sky. You’ll examine one of the most famous constellations, Orion, who the Ancient Greeks believed was a huntsman placed among the stars by Zeus himself.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/orion', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5334054.mp4', '2016-01-04', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ae/f3/regular_aef30283-74eb-43e5-aac8-b25365494c62.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:19'),
(240, 'Cancer in the 21st Century: the Genomic Revolution', 'Discover how genetics is revolutionising the detection and treatment of cancer, with this free online course.', 'Cancer Research UK estimates that 1 in 2 people in the UK will be diagnosed with cancer during their lifetime. It is a disease that impacts on most people’s lives at some stage. So understanding cancer, and the development of new treatments, is of intrinsic interest to us all.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/cancer-and-the-genomic-revolution', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2958909.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/90/6f/regular_906f023f-dbe3-40ee-a8f5-2feb04c56828.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Glasgow', '2015-11-04 00:03:20'),
(241, 'Supply Chain Innovation: How Technology Can Create a Sustainable Future', 'Understand how new technologies can make supply chains more sustainable and learn how to deal with todays trends.', 'Every product that we use today is the result of a supply chain - a complex series of steps that turn raw materials into the final products we use and everything related with this. Managing these supply chains has become more and more a challenge, especially with all modern technologies and todays trends. The 24-hour economy, fast delivery of goods to your home, wanting to have customized products and of course the focus on sustainability are a few of these trends.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/supply-chain-innovation', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5282692.mp4', '2016-01-11', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c3/5f/regular_c35fa072-a305-4a64-8787-1529c1e13589.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Twente', '2015-11-04 00:03:20'),
(242, 'The Science of Nutrition', 'Explore the science behind what you eat with this free online course.', 'Are we really what we eat? And how do we know what is in our food?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-nutrition', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4686390.mp4', '2016-01-11', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/98/c1/regular_98c184c3-0cff-44b6-87dd-fe341fc2a65a.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:21'),
(243, 'Smart Cities', 'Explore the role of technology and data in cities, and learn how you can participate in the creation of smart cities.', 'Cities are incubators of innovation and opportunities but they also face great challenges such as rapid urbanisation, climate change and inequality. How can smart cities address these challenges and become more resilient? And what role will people play in the design and planning of our smart cities?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/smart-cities', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4320132.mp4', '2016-01-18', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c8/67/regular_c8674e50-15bc-424f-85ff-055fff956043.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:22'),
(244, 'Energy: Thermodynamics in Everyday Life', 'Understand the laws of thermodynamics – and how they govern how we use and lose energy everyday – in this free online course.', 'Energy is essential to life at many levels and its transformation from one form to another – whether in the cells of our bodies or the machines that enable modern society – is governed by the laws of thermodynamics.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5569610.mp4', '2016-02-01', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/71/62/regular_7162e433-558b-47e2-b263-195f8be0f45b.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'no', 'University of Liverpool', '2015-11-04 00:03:22'),
(245, 'Gravity! From the Big Bang to Black Holes', 'Gravity runs the Universe. This free online course explains why, focussing on key concepts from the Big Bang to black holes.', 'What is gravity? This fundamental force is the common theme between concepts as intriguing as the Big Bang, black holes, dark energy, space-time, gravitational waves and the expansion of the Universe.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/gravity', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4654030.mp4', '2015-10-26', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/57/ea/regular_57ea9287-4b25-4f25-a151-611222cce8ec.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Paris Diderot', '2015-11-04 00:03:23'),
(246, 'Identifying Food Fraud', 'An introduction to modern analytical science techniques and how they can be used to uncover food fraud.', 'The food industry is one of the most important commercial sectors in the world. Everyone uses it, but how many people abuse it? As we witness the increasing globalisation of the supply chain, a growing challenge is verifying the questionable identity of raw materials in the food we eat.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/food-fraud', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4991864.mp4', '2015-10-26', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/be/4e/regular_be4e9062-2ba7-4c63-82b9-d542370dccf0.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:03:24'),
(247, 'Numeracy Skills for Employability and the Workplace', 'Improve your mathematical confidence and gain the skills to pass employers’ numeracy tests with this free online course.', 'In our highly technical world numeracy skills, particularly the ability to interpret data, are becoming increasingly important and are highly sought after by employers.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/numeracy-skills', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3100937.mp4', '2015-10-19', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ef/ee/regular_efeeb9bf-a129-455c-a1f0-f4727d81bf2b.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Loughborough University', '2015-11-04 00:03:24'),
(248, 'Moons', 'Explore the many moons of our Solar System. Find out what makes them special. Should we send humans to our Moon again?', 'There are lots of moons in our Solar System. The Earth is the only planet with just a single moon. Some moons are bigger than ours; many are much smaller. There are even tiny moons orbiting some of the asteroids. Some have ongoing volcanic eruptions; others are dead, heavily cratered lumps. One has rivers and lakes of liquid methane. Our own Moon has resources that could help open the Solar System for future exploration. A small handful of moons have conditions below their surfaces where primitive life might exist.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/moons', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2096693.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/45/58/regular_45589460-fec1-4b42-96d9-ecd89c0a4e13.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:25'),
(249, 'Data to Insight: An Introduction to Data Analysis', 'This course is a hands-on introduction to statistical data analysis that emphasises fundamental concepts and practical skills.', 'Organisations around the world are collecting more data than ever. They are talking about big data, data science, business intelligence, analytics, data mining and data visualisation, and there’s an urgent need for people with the data skills to understand, interpret and communicate this information.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/data-to-insight', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1644667.mp4', '2015-10-19', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e5/09/regular_e50950a6-e653-4933-9443-6a25900440be.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Auckland', '2015-11-04 00:03:25'),
(250, 'Maths for Humans: Linear, Quadratic & Inverse Relations', 'Strengthen your algebra, geometry and thinking skills by learning about the maths behind real-world relations.', 'What’s the connection between the size of a city and the number of gas stations in it? How would you describe this relationship? How would you try to visualise and understand it?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/maths-linear-quadratic', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5061728.mp4', '2015-10-12', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c7/29/regular_c7294421-21da-4753-a06e-cb9abb3714d8.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UNSW Australia', '2015-11-04 00:03:26'),
(251, 'Ultrasound Imaging: What Is Inside?', 'Understand the technology of ultrasound, see how it is used in clinical practice and learn how to improve medical imaging.', 'Ultrasound is an easy and quick technique to visualize structures inside the human body. It is a relatively harmless and accessible technique. It has been used for decades in medical practice.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ultrasound-imaging', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4508377.mp4', '2015-10-05', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e1/39/regular_e1390375-f5b0-4893-9edf-3d36671ec508.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Twente', '2015-11-04 00:03:27'),
(252, 'Smart Cities', 'Explore the role of technology and data in cities, and learn how you can participate in the creation of smart cities.', 'Cities are incubators of innovation and opportunities but they also face great challenges such as rapid urbanisation, climate change and inequality. How can smart cities address these challenges and become more resilient? And what role will people play in the design and planning of our smart cities?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/smart-cities', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4320132.mp4', '2015-09-28', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fe/2e/regular_fe2ebb01-4e0a-44ec-bbc9-490420a8017f.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:27'),
(253, 'Assessment for Learning in STEM Teaching', 'A free online course led by Dylan Wiliam and Christine Harrison, to help STEM teachers get to grips with Assessment for Learning.', 'Assessment for Learning is a term that’s widely used in education, but applied in ways that are variable in their effectiveness. This free online course - designed for STEM teachers in primary and secondary schools, and sixth form and further education (FE) colleges - will help you understand and use it more effectively.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/assessment-for-learning', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428566.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/49/67/regular_49671185-1361-47f7-b320-5e36fe2a2883.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:28'),
(254, 'Basic Science: Understanding Experiments', 'This hands-on course introduces you to science-based skills through simple and exciting physics, chemistry and biology experiments', 'This practical, hands-on course aims to help you start thinking like a scientist by carrying out experiments at home and making scientific observations.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/science-experiments', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1631019.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/35/c4/regular_35c4e997-3fb2-4a60-b9ea-6c7d8741d04d.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:28'),
(255, 'Begin Robotics', 'Explore the history, anatomy and intelligence of robots with this free online course. Test drive robots using exciting simulations', 'Robots today are roving Mars, collecting data in dangerous environments, hoovering our floors, lifting patients in hospital, building cars and entertaining us in films. And, if you share Bill Gates and Stephen Hawking’s world view, the super intelligent ones may one day bring about the end of the human race.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/begin-robotics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3697356.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/82/ce/regular_82ce6165-30a4-440e-ad57-a7e8f9e77220.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:03:29'),
(256, 'Causes of Climate Change', 'Understand the physical processes behind climate variations in the past, present and future, with this free online course', 'This free online course provides the basis for understanding the underlying physical processes governing climate variations in the past, present and future.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/causes-of-climate-change', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4147256.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a1/84/regular_a184ac4b-f773-4ba7-87bb-fb9a23b1792c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bergen', '2015-11-04 00:03:30'),
(257, 'Climate Change: Challenges and Solutions', 'This course aims to explain the science of climate change, the risks it poses and the solutions available to reduce those risks.', 'The course is aimed at the level of students entering university, and seeks to provide an inter-disciplinary introduction to what is a broad field. It engages a number of experts from the University of Exeter and a number of partner organisations.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/climate-change-challenges-and-solutions', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2136990.mp4', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/cb/71/regular_cb71114d-b163-4486-908d-20dadfde623e.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Exeter', '2015-11-04 00:03:30'),
(258, 'Decision Making in a Complex and Uncertain World', 'This course will teach you the first principles of complexity, uncertainty and how to make decisions in a complex world.', 'Leaders must be able to act in a complex world and under uncertainty. This course is a first step to develop yourself into one of the future’s key decision makers or to enhance your decision-making skills.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/complexity-and-uncertainty', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2182037.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f6/28/regular_f6280438-ac86-4f67-9ff2-6d5bdda3e9ea.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Groningen', '2015-11-04 00:03:31'),
(259, 'Discover Dentistry', 'An entertaining and illuminating course for everyone to explore the impact dentistry has on our lives.', 'How important is a smile? Ever wondered what all those letters and numbers a dentist calls out during your check-up mean? How are broken teeth fixed, or how dentures are made? Join Dr Christopher Stokes on a learning journey to explore the dental profession and the impact dentistry has on all our lives.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/discover-dentistry', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3951348.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c9/0a/regular_c90a27ee-232d-4bd6-bc98-aa66ec60d481.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:03:31'),
(260, 'Dysphagia: Swallowing Difficulties and Medicines', 'This course will enhance the knowledge of any person involved in the administration of medicines to patients with dysphagia.', 'The course offers an opportunity to network with other learners and with the creators of the course through discussions, graphs and social networking features and to share knowledge with other learners and professionals. By completing this online course participants will be able to describe:', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dysphagia', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3261218.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/16/6c/regular_166c19c9-7eab-48da-b7b8-c21e383c1f58.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:03:32'),
(261, 'Ebola in Context: Understanding Transmission, Response and Control', 'How has the Ebola outbreak become a humanitarian emergency? Learn about the science behind the crisis.', 'In 2014, Ebola went from a scarcely known virus to the subject of daily news reports. The epidemic in West Africa has quickly surpassed all previous outbreaks, to become an unprecedented humanitarian crisis.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ebola-in-context', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2714612.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/46/1b/regular_461b7c93-fba6-4151-a140-cbdf9422c2bf.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine', '2015-11-04 00:03:32'),
(262, 'Ebola: Symptoms, History and Origins', 'Learn about Ebola, its symptoms, where it came from and what the current outbreak has taught us, with this free online course.', 'In December 2013, the largest outbreak of Ebola virus disease (EVD) that the world has ever seen, began in West Africa - a region of the continent that has historically been free of it.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/ebola', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3089045.mp4', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d9/5e/regular_d95ef0b5-c747-4815-bcde-26ebc3d0f87d.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:03:33'),
(263, 'Elements of Renewable Energy', 'Learn how sustainable energy from the Greek elements – Earth, Air, Fire and Water – can replace fossil fuels and nuclear power.', 'In recent decades there’s been increasing global concern about the sustainability of our use of fossil fuels and nuclear power, which has led to increased interest in more sustainable renewable energy sources.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/elements-renewable-energies', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0e/e1/regular_0ee1deec-38ac-46df-82a5-4d4b0f0bad4c.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:34'),
(264, 'Exploring Anatomy: the Human Abdomen', 'Explore the anatomy of the human abdomen and understand its clinical importance.', 'This course introduces you to the human abdomen and explores its many complex structures. As the course progresses, the structure and function of important organs will be demonstrated, discussed and related to common surgical scenarios and current research. Each of the three weeks will focus on a specific area of the abdomen; starting at the surface you will then enter the abdomen and be able to detail the anatomy of numerous organs including the stomach and liver.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/anatomy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2321495.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/0c/d4/regular_0cd42bec-6ea7-425f-9306-c84c455c8c6f.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:35');
INSERT INTO `course_data` (`id`, `title`, `short_desc`, `long_desc`, `course_link`, `video_link`, `start_date`, `course_length`, `course_image`, `category`, `site`, `course_fee`, `language`, `certificate`, `university`, `time_scraped`) VALUES
(265, 'Exploring Our Oceans', 'Explore the half of our world covered by deep ocean, and how our lives affect the hidden face of our planet.', 'The first astronauts to leave the Earth’s orbit saw our “blue planet” for the first time. But what lies in the half of our world covered by water more than two miles deep? How are our everyday lives connected to the ocean depths, and what challenges and opportunities does this previously hidden realm hold for our future?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/exploring-our-oceans', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d9/e6/regular_d9e61125-ca2d-4240-abba-751ca981345f.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:03:35'),
(266, 'Forensic Science and Criminal Justice', 'Learn how police use science in criminal investigations and its role in the criminal justice system with this free online course.', 'Over the past two decades, the criminal justice system has been dramatically affected by technological advances in scientific contributions to the law. The most influential developments have been in the area of DNA profiling, and its forensic applications for both identifying perpetrators and exonerating the innocent.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/forensic-crim-justice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2493477.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/f7/63/regular_f76375a2-d1f5-4625-b706-1b5b5e3a67f9.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leicester', '2015-11-04 00:03:36'),
(267, 'Getting a Grip on Mathematical Symbolism', 'Want to be an engineer or scientist? Lack mathematical confidence? Learn to think mathematically and explore essential concepts.', 'This course is aimed at those who aspire to study science or engineering foundation courses at university level. It draws upon the experience of staff from the Mathematics Education Centre at Loughborough University - a centre that has specialised for many years in mathematics teaching and mathematics support for science and engineering students who find the transition to university mathematics particularly challenging.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/mathematical-symbolism', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2344107.mp4', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/95/49/regular_95497a58-f83d-4043-992d-1fea57d922ca.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Loughborough University', '2015-11-04 00:03:38'),
(268, 'Identifying the Dead: Forensic Science and Human Identification', 'Uncover a grave, examine remains and reveal the victim’s identity in this free online course, linked to a new Val McDermid story.', 'The first step in any investigation involving a death is to determine the identity of the deceased. This free online course will take you on a journey through the world of forensic anthropology, unveiling the tools that will allow you to reveal that identity.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/identifying-the-dead', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4188357.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/9c/c5/regular_9cc5596f-9ebf-4c55-a426-0d2aee889f95.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Dundee', '2015-11-04 00:03:39'),
(269, 'Inside Cancer: How Genes Influence Cancer Development', 'Understand how genetics influence the development and spread of cancer, with this free, introductory online course.', 'Cancer is a disease that affects around one-third of the human population, irrespective of nationality or ethnic origins. There are many types of cancer, but they all have one thing in common - they begin as rebel or mutant cells.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/inside-cancer', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2285126.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/17/73/regular_1773392a-c546-49f6-b52a-bee15ce2a57a.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Bath', '2015-11-04 00:03:40'),
(270, 'Introduction to Forensic Science', 'Methods & scientific underpinning of forensic science, from crime scene investigation to reporting evidential value within a case.', 'The course addresses four major evidence types: drugs of abuse, DNA, firearms and impression evidence, and discusses these through the exploration of a case-based scenario presented across a six-week modular framework.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/introduction-to-forensic-science', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3055990.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/25/6b/regular_256bf98e-3ae2-4836-a7fb-350b393568f8.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Strathclyde', '2015-11-04 00:03:41'),
(271, 'Kitchen chemistry', 'Use your kitchen as a laboratory to learn about chemistry using everyday chemicals.', 'The Kitchen Chemistry course is designed to explore some of the principles of chemistry. You will be encouraged to carry out your own experiments using materials that are often found in the home. If not they can be obtained from most supermarkets, pharmacies or hardware stores.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/kitchen-chemistry', 'http://view.vzaar.com/1472601.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/32/bf/regular_32bfe603-fb54-4557-8a38-c112feab03eb.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:03:42'),
(272, 'Metabolomics: Understanding Metabolism in the 21st Century', 'Discover how metabolomics is revolutionising our understanding of metabolism with this free online course.', 'Metabolomics is an emerging field that aims to measure the complement of metabolites (the intermediates and products of metabolism) in living organisms. The complement of metabolites in a biological system is known as the metabolome and represents the downstream effect of an organism’s genome and its interaction with the environment. Metabolomics has a wide application area across the medical and biological sciences and is attractive to both new and established scientists. In this course we will provide an introduction to metabolomics, explain why we want to study the metabolome and describe the current challenges in analysing the complement of metabolites in a biological system. We will describe the interdisciplinary approaches adopted in the metabolomics workflow and demonstrate how the combined efforts of scientist’s from different disciplines is advancing this exciting field. By the end of the course the learner will understand how metabolomics can revolutionise our understanding of metabolism.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/metabolomics', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4782792.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e3/84/regular_e384a622-583e-4778-b412-78614e422023.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:03:43'),
(273, 'Soils: Introducing the World Beneath Our Feet', 'Learn about soils, the variety of life they contain and how humans impact this fragile system, with this free online course.', 'Soils are a vital part of our planet’s functioning, but all too often we take soils for granted. In this free online course, we introduce you to soils and explore the world beneath our feet.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/soils', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3693052.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/42/e6/regular_42e6e9b4-5a4f-43b4-bd68-ecd46f957777.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:03:44'),
(274, 'The Discovery of the Higgs Boson', 'Should we be excited about the Higgs boson? Find out more about particle physics and understanding the universe.', 'The discovery of a new fundamental particle at the Large Hadron Collider (LHC), CERN is the latest step in a long quest seeking to answer one of physics’ most enduring questions: why do particles have mass? The experiments’ much anticipated success confirms predictions made decades earlier by Peter Higgs and others, and offers a glimpse into a universe of physics beyond the Standard Model.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/higgs', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2181886.mp4', '0000-00-00', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/c3/08/regular_c308b27f-50ab-4d87-9d3d-c530c07f3a69.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Edinburgh', '2015-11-04 00:03:45'),
(275, 'The Science of Medicines', 'Learn the science behind how and why medicines work, and what can improve patients treatment, with this free online course.', 'The world’s growing population faces major health issues, and medicines are a primary pillar to effect better health. Learn about the science of key medicines used to manage heart disease, depression, diabetes, pain control and smoking cessation.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-medicines', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a3/2d/regular_a32d14b8-c30d-4218-b151-b0a596206f68.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Monash University', '2015-11-04 00:03:46'),
(276, 'The Science of Nuclear Energy', 'Discover the science behind nuclear energy and its role in energy provision in the past, present and future.', 'With the need to reduce carbon emissions around the world, the way we generate our power has to change and nuclear energy is back on the political agenda. But do you know your fission from your fusion? Would you like the knowledge to make an informed decision?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/the-science-of-nuclear-energy', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3933347.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2c/51/regular_2c51f90d-2504-47bb-8816-c834b4e29b99.jpg', 'Maths, Science & Engineering', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:46'),
(277, 'Football: More than a Game', 'Explore the role of football in the world today - including finances, clubs, nations and rivalries - with this free online course.', 'At the beginning of the twentieth century, football was the most popular game in the western world and has since grown to become a global spectacle.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/football', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3057075.mp4', '2016-01-25', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/90/2d/regular_902d0c48-095e-4919-81aa-4b8f4d3f198c.jpg', 'Leisure & Sports', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Edinburgh', '2015-11-04 00:03:47'),
(278, 'Exploring Play: The Importance of Play in Everyday Life', 'Understanding the nature and value of play through the course of our lives, across cultures and communities.', 'Play your part… Play the fool… All work and no play… Child’s play… Fair play… Play a joke… Play with fire…', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/play', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5053351.mp4', '2015-10-19', 7, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/67/b9/regular_67b9b2fa-8b51-49bd-9327-005da7f4a2ef.jpg', 'Leisure & Sports', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:03:48'),
(279, 'Blended Learning Essentials: Getting Started', 'A free course for the Vocational Education and Training sector to promote effective practice and pedagogy in blended learning.', 'If you are working in further education, skills training, vocational education, workplace learning, lifelong learning or adult education, this free online course is designed to help you understand the benefits of blended learning and how to make more effective use of technology to support your learners.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/blended-learning-getting-started', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5003250.mp4', '2015-11-02', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/2d/f4/regular_2df4a5a6-f997-4bd1-80f4-b47ac4d22fcb.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:49'),
(280, 'How to Succeed at: Interviews', 'This free three week course provides the tools you need to succeed at interviews and land your dream job or course place.', 'This course will help you to succeed at interviews, whether you are applying for jobs or planning to study. Because being offered an interview can be quite daunting, we’ve put together a set of materials to help you prepare and be successful on the day.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/interviews', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3030237.mp4', '2015-11-16', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e1/6a/regular_e16aaa55-5f57-43f6-801f-cccc179f1e21.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:03:50'),
(281, 'Get Started with Online Learning', 'This free online course will explain how you can study online without putting the rest of your life on hold.', 'The internet is playing a bigger role in our lives, as we buy our groceries, manage our finances, share social experiences and otherwise live our lives online. But how many of us have considered studying online?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/online-learning', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4763094.mp4', '2016-01-04', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/ce/19/regular_ce19db60-1224-442e-9df3-e38913259994.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The Open University', '2015-11-04 00:03:51'),
(282, 'A Beginners Guide to Writing in English for University Study', 'Learn how to use English for study at university or college and develop your writing skills, vocabulary and grammar.', 'If you’re interested in studying at university or college in an English-speaking country, you’ll need to learn how to write using academic English. Academic writing can be very different from other types of English writing you may have done in the past. We have developed this course to help you learn the basics of academic writing and develop your English skills for study in the UK, US, Australia or other countries where English is used.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/english-for-study', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2840424.mp4', '2016-01-18', 5, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a7/4c/regular_a74c84a4-b484-4372-ae31-4db7c100529b.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Reading', '2015-11-04 00:03:53'),
(283, 'Preparing for University', 'This course will help develop the key skills required for a smooth transition to university.', 'Higher education is about learning at a higher level: developing skills relating to critical thinking; holding a supported, substantive argument; analysing and using data or sources critically. These are university-level skills but you can work on the foundations of these skills before you get there. Such skills will also help in assessments such as A-levels and extended project work. They are also attributes that employers value in graduates.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/preparing-for-uni', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3053360.mp4', '2016-01-25', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/9a/f1/regular_9af1f97a-31b3-4d40-947e-22a28eed8370.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:03:53'),
(284, 'Teaching Literacy Through Film', 'Learn how to use film in the classroom, teach literacy and improve both reading and writing skills, with this free online course', 'Why use film to teach literacy? This free online course, led by film education experts from the British Film Institute (BFI) and film education charity Into Film, will examine the debate surrounding film as a vehicle for teaching literacy, alongside recent evidence demonstrating significant improvements in children’s reading and writing through use of film texts.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/teaching-literacy-through-film', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5531364.mp4', '2016-01-25', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/24/cf/regular_24cf4d7a-2552-4a69-862c-32c3c941ad99.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The British Film Institute (BFI)', '2015-11-04 00:03:54'),
(285, 'Academic Integrity: Values, Skills, Action', 'This course will explore academic integrity and how you can demonstrate it in your work, study and research at university.', 'What is academic integrity? Why is it so important in academia? And how can you, as a student at university, achieve with integrity and honesty?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/academic-integrity', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2684892.mp4', '2016-02-01', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/e9/03/regular_e903f210-2e65-4bd9-bbd2-67e80e17a0d1.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Auckland', '2015-11-04 00:03:55'),
(286, 'Blended Learning Essentials: Embedding Practice', 'This is the second part of a course for the Vocational Education and Training sector to promote effective use of blended learning.', 'This is the second part of the Blended Learning Essentials course, which will build upon the content of the first part, covering issues such as learning from experience and tackling difficult challenges with the help of blended learning.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/blended-learning-embedding-practice', 'http://view.vzaar.com/5559266.mp4', '2016-02-01', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/29/04/regular_2904f7f4-b0e0-449b-a860-5a49bb2e5aed.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:03:55'),
(287, 'What is Character? Virtue Ethics in Education', 'Explore important questions about character education and how it contributes to individual and societal flourishing.', 'Character education is increasingly being talked about by politicians, employers, teachers, parents and young people across the world. Can teaching virtues such as honesty, self-control, fairness, resilience and respect - which contribute to good character - be part of the solution to many of the challenges facing society today?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/what-is-character', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2159171.mp4', '2015-10-26', 2, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/b8/39/regular_b839d53f-5708-44c5-be0d-a7b7e421b9c9.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Birmingham', '2015-11-04 00:03:56'),
(288, 'How to Succeed at: Writing Applications', 'This free three week course will help you produce a perfect CV, application and online profile when applying for a job or course.', 'This course will help you to write successful applications, whether you are applying for jobs or planning to study at university or college.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/writing-applications', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3030168.mp4', '2015-10-26', 3, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/fa/28/regular_fa284db2-d323-432d-8930-3ef8addefcb4.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Sheffield', '2015-11-04 00:03:56'),
(289, 'Understanding Language: Learning and Teaching', 'An introduction to some key concepts in the effective teaching and learning of languages.', 'What is language? How do we learn meaning in a new language? What is easy and hard about learning another language? And what is the best way to teach other languages?', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/understanding-language', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2497255.mp4', '2015-10-19', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/8d/f5/regular_8df536e7-bcbf-45eb-8599-d8aa0da56616.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:03:57'),
(290, 'Logical and Critical Thinking', 'Improve your logical and critical thinking skills in this free online course. Identify common obstacles to effective thinking.', 'We are constantly being given reasons to do and believe things: to believe that we should buy a product, support a cause, accept a job, judge someone innocent or guilty, that fairness requires us to do some household chore, and so on. Assessing the reasons we are given to do or believe these things calls upon us to think critically and logically.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/logical-and-critical-thinking', 'http://view.vzaar.com/4129686.mp4', '2015-09-28', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a4/5e/regular_a45e1791-4619-4c75-a5eb-98ee33da42b1.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'The University of Auckland', '2015-11-04 00:03:58'),
(291, 'Preparing for University', 'This course will help develop the key skills required for a smooth transition to university.', 'Higher education is about learning at a higher level: developing skills relating to critical thinking; holding a supported, substantive argument; analysing and using data or sources critically. These are university-level skills but you can work on the foundations of these skills before you get there. Such skills will also help in assessments such as A-levels and extended project work. They are also attributes that employers value in graduates.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/preparing-for-uni', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3053360.mp4', '2015-09-28', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/9a/f1/regular_9af1f97a-31b3-4d40-947e-22a28eed8370.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:03:59'),
(292, 'Developing Your Research Project', 'Undertaking an Extended Project Qualification, IB extended essay or any other scholarly research? This guides you step-by-step.', 'Curiosity is one of humanity’s most important characteristics. It has enabled us to make the unknown known, to break barriers and to shine a light on all aspects of life, from our day to day hobbies to the exploration of the stars. Our innate desire to explore is responsible for many of our proudest achievements. This course will help train you to harness your curiosity and use it to undertake your own research projects in a scholarly manner.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/research-project', 'http://view.vzaar.com/3028851.mp4', '2015-09-14', 8, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/09/ac/regular_09ac5f73-22ae-4186-a8e7-b74d9702f1ac.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Southampton', '2015-11-04 00:04:00'),
(293, 'Assessment for Learning in STEM Teaching', 'A free online course led by Dylan Wiliam and Christine Harrison, to help STEM teachers get to grips with Assessment for Learning.', 'Assessment for Learning is a term that’s widely used in education, but applied in ways that are variable in their effectiveness. This free online course - designed for STEM teachers in primary and secondary schools, and sixth form and further education (FE) colleges - will help you understand and use it more effectively.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/assessment-for-learning', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2428566.mp4', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/49/67/regular_49671185-1361-47f7-b320-5e36fe2a2883.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'University of Leeds', '2015-11-04 00:04:01'),
(294, 'Dyslexia and Foreign Language Teaching', 'Gain practical tools and theoretical insights to help dyslexic students learn second languages, with this free online course.', 'Dyslexia affects 10-15% of the population. Dyslexic students are often either exempted from the study of additional languages or they underperform in foreign language classes.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/dyslexia', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2555787.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/67/6c/regular_676cb58f-d5b5-4b13-9aa1-7b8bb2477e99.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'Lancaster University', '2015-11-04 00:04:01'),
(295, 'Professional Practices for English Language Teaching', 'A free online continuing professional development (CPD) course for people who are teaching English as a foreign language.', 'This free online course is for English language teachers around the world. It will help you develop the skills and practices you need for your continuing professional development (CPD).', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/english-language-teaching', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/a9/cf/regular_a9cf89ec-1531-4cfe-839c-a23cbabfdea2.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'British Council', '2015-11-04 00:04:02'),
(296, 'Study Skills for International Students', 'A course looking at key skills that international students need in order to be successful at a UK university.', 'This course looks at some of the key skills that international students need in order to be successful at a UK university. It is special because of the way it has been produced. Our English language and study skills teachers at INTO UEA surveyed and interviewed students who had already successfully completed a course and progressed to study at the University. We asked them about the things that they had found most challenging when they started their university programme. This course has been developed as a result of what those international students told us, as well as the experience INTO UEA colleagues have in preparing international students for university study.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/study-skills-for-international-students', 'http://view.vzaar.com/2042029.mp4', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/af/29/regular_af29b508-568e-46c0-a9a7-019969ae2223.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:04:03'),
(297, 'Teaching Computing', 'A free online course for primary and secondary school teachers who are tackling the Computing curriculum in England.', 'This free online course aims to help teachers in primary schools and at Key Stage 3, who are delivering the Computing curriculum, which was introduced to schools in England in September 2014.', 'https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/teaching-computing', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://ugc.futurelearn.com/uploads/images/d2/c5/regular_d2c51ff2-0c67-41aa-ab9c-10e9c1835f4e.jpg', 'Studying & Teaching', 'FutureLearn.com', 0, 'english', 'yes', 'UEA (University of East Anglia)', '2015-11-04 00:04:04'),
(298, 'Android Development for Beginners', 'Learn the basics of Android and Java programming, and take the first step on your journey to becoming an Android developer!', 'To access the free version of this course, click the blue button that says Access Course Materials.Learn the basics of Android and Java programming, and take the first step on your journey to becoming an Android developer! This course is designed for students who are new to programming, and want to learn how to build Android apps. You dont need any programming experience to take this course. If youve been using a smartphone to surf the web and chat with friends, then youre our perfect target student! Learning anything new can be tough. We will walk you through the process of making Android apps, but to get the most out of this course, you must bring your enthusiasm for learning, and budget time on your calendar to learn with us.By the end of the course, youll build two simple (but powerful) apps that you can share with your friends. We also hope that you will learn enough through this course to decide how best to continue your journey as an Android app developer, if youre interesting in pursuing such a path.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/android-development-for-beginners--ud837?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/LzbzRqANeDH43wWQdi1Fp93S_q9Whw62QzmR1mo4Y7CxpF2WFy2KmNgjzqSiBgGMo96UzXBsstAvx6GIa7k=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(299, 'How to create in Android', 'Learn from a set of amazing, hand-picked Android tutorials and build an app that you will want to share with your friends and family.', 'Here is one important question Android developers ask while making apps: "How can I do ________ in Android?"The following are versions of this question that we came across recently: - How can I add radio buttons to my app? - How can I play a sound? - How can I navigate between multiple screens? This course is a collection of such questions and their answers. By the end of this course you will have mastered the ability to implement new Android features by reading a blog or article  this is a critical skill possessed by professional Android developers. As a result, you will also be able to use several User Interface components  like Toggle Buttons, Menus, Grid View and many more  that are central to making functional and delightful Android apps.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/how-to-create-anything-in-android--ud802?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/PGI733_nxuUzl8HycyhqlJrbTHMKD8JQwbfUHHxxWdM8YG_BaKnNnMLFzfpmHM54znBVHeLHUuEtO7mAdWI=s0#w=1725&h=1060', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(300, 'Developing Android Apps', 'Build a cloud-connected Android app, and learn the tools, principles, and best practices of mobile and Android development that youll apply to your own projects.', 'As the first course in the Android Developer Nanodegree, Developing Android Apps is the foundation of our advanced Android curriculum. This course blends theory and practice to help you build great apps the right way. In this course, youll work with instructors step-by-step to build a cloud-connected Android app, and learn best practices of mobile development, and Android development in particular.####[Download Udacitys Android app](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.udacity.android) to keep learning wherever you go!', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/developing-android-apps--ud853?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LfVBFFoy9Y0', '0000-00-00', 10, 'https://lh6.ggpht.com/57QPWoDnN4dSulg4tqC_pFHcN5pmUIzyrXyu3TiirP1JRCQ36fzz6IgEPl2HdMZ3GIrc80rRzAkRiPUyOXM=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(301, 'Advanced Android App Development', 'Make your app production-ready by applying advanced features like library integration, material design, widgets, receiving cloud messages, and more!', 'This course will guide you through the process of productionizing an app, using Sunshine, the weather app we built in Developing Android Apps. Following Androids Core App Quality Guidelines, well identify the production criteria that still needs to be implemented, then tackle each problem until Sunshine is ready to publish on the Google Play Store. In the process, well introduce you to a host of tools and concepts, including: material design approaches, image-handling, performance profiling, and more!', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/advanced-android-app-development--ud855?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-GpqtaqrSzJmmVv4n0NPiLBHv6VXv1ThyGeB4VFTd-S65c11SBzBdkAG9quCsv4zof62AjzlycEo0SR-CdA=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(302, 'Gradle for Android and Java', 'Build bigger and better Android and Java apps using the Gradle build tool.', 'This course explores how the Gradle build tool compiles and packages apps, and youll learn to customize the build process. The first half of this course is for anyone interested in Gradle, build automation, and continuous delivery of software.The latter half of the course reveals the magic that happens after you hit the "Run" button in Android Studio. Youll also explore advanced Android topics, learning to configure free vs paid app flavors, create and integrate Android libraries, test your app, and prepare your app for the Play Store.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/gradle-for-android-and-java--ud867?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 6, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/jeVezk1wHnPay4E48RN4S-PMhIfZl-pVkY0j0xD_IrTSVJ5lvqn7erid1iZggX7jlI39UsB6hEDG6NgHk3c=s0#w=1682&h=1034', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(303, 'Google Play Services: Location & Context', 'Enhance your apps with Googles Fused Location Provider, Activity Recognition, and Geofencing API capabilities.', 'Vitally important for building the best possible mobile app, the Location and Context API allows your Android app behavior to change based on location. In this course, youll learn how to implement this with the Fused Location Provider, which gives you much more than simple GPS. Youll also learn about Activity recognition, which allows you to tailor your app to what the user is doing. Finally, youll learn about Geofencing, and how location services work alongside geofences to allow you to build apps that could be used for augmented reality!**This course is part of the Google Play Services series, which features a variety of different Google APIs. Designed as standalone short courses, you can take any course on its own, or take them all!*** **Google Play Services: Location and Context** [this course] * Google Play Services: Analytics* Google Play Services: AdMob * Google Play Services: Maps * Google Play Services: Identity', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/google-play-services-location-context--ud876-1?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Du089YR8t4H5dgnPKvNL0qjwUUjxFVPkt6q6s3kLWbV1ezEDSMeH0HJ-JrLFUyFawcwi_q7ZU3wXArZDGsiq=s0#w=1440&h=811', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(304, 'Google Play Services: Analytics', 'Where in the world are people using your app? And how are they using your app? Take this course to learn how to answer these questions!', 'Where in the world are people using your app? Which activities do they use most? How do they navigate through your app? Take this course to learn how to add code to your mobile app to send usage data to Google Analytics, and get answers to questions like these.This course also covers how to use Google Tag Manager to send updated information to your app without needing to redeploy the APK, and to manage all your Google Analytics tags.**This course is part of the Google Play Services series, which features a variety of different Google APIs. Designed as standalone short courses, you can take any course on its own, or take them all!*** Google Play Services: Location and Context * **Google Play Services: Analytics** [this course]* Google Play Services: AdMob * Google Play Services: Maps * Google Play Services: Identity', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/google-play-services-analytics--ud876-2?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/4dVAU-fDZoNLh8H4XTmblZz5yFsOXxY9tWCmudPwyeB-XlY-Qr30tUUlD7QkBG9JWKfggmG53uGJQ_hKMWLd=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(305, 'Google Play Services: AdMob', 'Learn how to monetize apps using Googles AdMob to display banner and interstitial ads!', 'In this course, you will learn how to monetize apps using Googles AdMob to display banner and interstitial ads.**This course is part of the Google Play Services series, which features a variety of different Google APIs. Designed as standalone short courses, you can take any course on its own, or take them all!*** Google Play Services: Location and Context * Google Play Services: Analytics * **Google Play Services: AdMob** [this course]* Google Play Services: Maps * Google Play Services: Identity', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/google-play-services-admob--ud876-3?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/SbN466LXIXxxFePWHPtcZIMJkhXvfGxMEvFTrqVnGtcATyFPvuwV5-UBWsnUF3cPxk9KBPyZQH45E1piPxfh=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(306, 'Google Play Services: Maps', 'Maps on mobile devices have changed the world for millions of users. Learn how to use the Google Maps API to extend this functionality to your apps.', 'In this course, youll learn everything from how to add maps to your Android app, to how to build a virtual hike down the Grand Canyon!**This course is part of the Google Play Services series, which features a variety of different Google APIs. Designed as standalone short courses, you can take any course on its own, or take them all!*** Google Play Services: Location and Context * Google Play Services: Analytics* Google Play Services: AdMob * **Google Play Services: Maps** [this course]* Google Play Services: Identity', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/google-play-services-maps--ud876-4?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/l8dRGuY5xlIMuGmjxX9DSYwn80BYsR3UwlTuNrAXuqMU__3SqO19cAnLwCZi5QEWsyTvhqFTOebVwgq0IbI=s0#w=1440&h=809', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(307, 'Google Play Services: Identity', 'Use Googles Identity Platform in your apps to build a seamless sign-in experience and access user-permitted metadata.', 'In this course, youll learn how to use Googles Identity Platform to allow users to sign-in using their Google credentials, and how to access data that they grant you permission to access. **This course is part of the Google Play Services series, which features a variety of different Google APIs. Designed as standalone short courses, you can take any course on its own, or take them all!*** Google Play Services: Location and Context* Google Play Services: Analytics* Google Play Services: AdMob * Google Play Services: Maps * **Google Play Services: Identity** [this course]', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/google-play-services-identity--ud876-5?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/eqVVduu3Q-Qy9IE9SjgevG-mp2RY9yiM9arsHVw4BYCJgxPT6hE-a5pQCjhIDYQcxvQ0XRqs4KedGJy6G-4=s0#w=1438&h=810', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(308, 'Android Performance', 'Performance matters to users, so it must matter to you. Learn how to identify and fix bottlenecks in your Android applications, and ensure a smooth user experience.', 'If youve ever hit performance issues that affect your apps usability, this course will teach you how to identify and diagnose your performance problems. By the end of this course, youll be able to perform exploratory tests, run profiling tools, use outputs to navigate to problematic code, and design a plan of attack to mitigate poor performance. Youll also gain a higher level of understanding about how program code and the Android platform interact, which will help you optimize for performance in the future.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/android-performance--ud825?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aUGHKLzBnrpJaHbnGVSRShnAj6GqDXoNMRG13-RJfHjw0LJOyEpPSsxGLxOdjwBVji02tcATbfmn2l50rUg=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(309, 'Material Design for Android Developers', 'Learn and apply the material design principles that define Androids visual language to your apps.', 'In this course, youll learn how to apply the material design principles that define Androids visual language to your apps. Well start by walking you through Android design fundamentals, then well show you how to apply this knowledge to transform design elements of sample apps. By the end of the course, youll understand how to create and use material design elements, surfaces, transitions and graphics in your app, across multiple form factors.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/material-design-for-android-developers--ud862?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/_nio_GWBSc0BCCk_aHyBn766-ddp1mrod05GJzQSAA_IkWQ7Uxfv33OFJfMJU5uULj3V01AfT3e6YgFGcg=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(310, 'Android Wear Development', 'Learn how to extend your app to Android Wear smartwatches, allowing you to reach users wherever and whenever theyd want or need your app.', 'Extending your app to Android Wear smart watches allows you to reach your users wherever and whenever theyd want or need your app. As youll learn in this course, you can take your existing Android development experience and apply it to developing for Android Wear. This course will take you through getting started, application structure, and information sharing between the wearable and the companion phone or the cloud. Well also give you the knowledge necessary for designing great user experiences for wearables including how to take advantage of the always-on display of Android Wear devices.This course is part of the Ubiquitous Computing series. Designed as standalone short courses, you can take any course on its own, or take them all!* **Android Wear Development** [this course]* Android TV and Google Cast Development* Android Auto Development', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/android-wear-development--ud875A?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/n2A2iq0wCQDp4CNt34z3Yu9_4UsdDa_zTF-M4ZGojDjNGlAVfBFKd9YBJdofTpFM-sS8cXFUCJUVjtoM5pY=s0#w=1758&h=1080', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(311, 'Android TV and Google Cast Development', 'Go where your users are: the living room! This course shows you how to extend your existing Android app to also work on Android TV, and/or with Google Cast.', 'Go where your users are: the living room! With Google Cast and Android TV, you can add a big screen and cinematic experience to your app. This course shows you how to extend your existing Android app to work on Android TV and Google Cast. You can take advantage of both technologies without having to rewrite your app.This course is part of the Ubiquitous Computing series. Designed as standalone short courses, you can take any course on its own, or take them all!* Android Wear Development* **Android TV and Google Cast Development** [this course]* Android Auto Development', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/android-tv-and-google-cast-development--ud875B?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 1, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/mXwOuGIoiOQxP4eXAKk8qt449JzBrjfr7X_IcEpoCEzJazPgGnhFKUmeQWIOsPIUa_zjCGaMaQHF0UfsEQc=s0#w=1706&h=1049', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(312, 'Android Auto Development', 'Reach your users while theyre out and about by extending your Media or Messaging app to Android Auto!', 'Reach your users while theyre out and about by extending your Media or Messaging app to Android Auto! As youll learn in this course, making your app available in the car is as easy as extending your existing code. This course explains how to get started and then covers Media and Messaging apps in detail.This course is part of the Ubiquitous Computing series. Designed as standalone short courses, you can take any course on its own, or take them all!* Android Wear Development* Android TV and Google Cast Development* **Android Auto Development** [this course]', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/android-auto-development--ud875C?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 1, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3lVfrfdzindeWt7gXkQrkDYtbYJuIMGuAo8Wrt3haxzNqxKOER3oK4hraiTJcNEHzJdnEEWsKbtqg-rguUs2=s0#w=1758&h=1080', 'Android', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(313, 'Product Design', 'Learn product validation, UI/UX practices, Googles Design Sprint and the process for setting and tracking actionable metrics.', 'There is nothing more powerful than an idea whose time has come. This course is designed to help you materialize your game-changing idea and transform it into a product that you can build a business around. Product Design blends theory and practice to teach you product validation, UI/UX practices, Googles Design Sprint and the process for setting and tracking actionable metrics.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/product-design--ud509?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/1RoMggIjpqstcLqFPS4anLDCXYSvhI1l_PObbgY1hzeDX9hnPhLMV7k515AWbePKNzllzFK8p6cvzM3lHco=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Non-Tech', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(314, 'App Monetization', 'Learn how to effectively develop, implement, and measure your monetization strategy, iterating on the model as appropriate.', 'There is no higher form of user validation than having customers support your product with their wallets. However, the path to a profitable business is not necessarily an easy one. This course blends instruction with real life examples to help you effectively develop, implement, and measure your monetization strategy, iterating on the model as appropriate.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/app-monetization--ud518?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/ExdtHAQwrj8I1RjVrJt78udW3xNYFzcyTqqi25Q_Q2h4GoWeSzA4UUJxMtkH3sfG2qydfm-2rZ6CLXYc_sA=s0#w=1200&h=738', 'Non-Tech', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(315, 'Rapid Prototyping', 'Learning to prototype will save you time and money in the development process. Youll create quality apps faster and have confidence in the viability of your products.', 'Prototyping allows you to spend ten minutes -- instead of ten hours -- finding an amazing design for your product. This course will guide you through the iterative process of prototyping an app and conducting user research. You will start by making a low fidelity paper prototype, conducting research with users, and using that research to inform your next iteration. Together with InVision well guide you through creating interactive prototypes. This means you dont have to code an app before putting it in front of users! Along the way, youll learn how and where prototyping fits into your app design process and how you can use prototyping to become a better entrepreneur.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/rapid-prototyping--ud723?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 3, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/XCike2QVT4WdczpGwDf0PC8BlEnbW6SO90FExI5bD243R6Djs7FeCsaFxpAPTAwdsJvjcHMXx8yEXm9U8ag=s0#w=1758&h=1080', 'Non-Tech', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(316, 'App Marketing', 'This course will help you organize a strategy of identifying your perfect user, and teach you how to grow your user base by focusing your product on their needs.', 'Without customers, your business does not exist. Marketing helps you understand your potential user and focus your product on their needs. This course will help you organize a strategy of identifying your perfect user, find ways to connect with them and what youll say when you find them. This covers research, planning, execution and most importantly how to grow your user base.**Available Now! Lesson 1: Understand the User**', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/app-marketing--ud719?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 2, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/9xu4a7fRWBue7q2dUvNEcyZ6bdIAnuB4SxfmAzLop9HZScBGFx0Z8eDW_EsBoXyvj-971aOkU7MqTFN0lfyO=s0#w=1724&h=1060', 'Non-Tech', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(317, '2D Game Development with LibGDX', 'This course explores how to use LibGDX to build 2D games that run anywhere, from web browsers to mobile devices. At the end you will create a full game, called Icicles.', 'This course explores how to use LibGDX to build 2D games that run anywhere, from web browsers to mobile devices. We start with simple drawings, and then turn to simple animations, physics, and user input handling. Finally, we create a full game, called Icicles, where icicles rain down from the top of the screen, and the player must dodge them using the arrow keys or by tilting their phone.', 'https://www.udacity.com/course/2d-game-development-with-libgdx--ud405?utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api', '', '0000-00-00', 8, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/NpCEkFwRBPGqMad350u4M4b96aenrM1H4qTmccbNkAofealSwciK9lLo9dup_JUtD0zY-teD6I8pjqVPqhk=s0#w=1324&h=814', '', 'http://www.udacity.com/', 0, 'english', 'no', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
