(3119, 'Climate Change: The Science', 'Do you want to talk about climate change from an informed perspective?', 'Do you want to talk about climate change from an informed perspective? Are you interested in how global warming works? Climate change is the biggest challenge of our time, and climate science is critical to finding solutions. How can we make the best decisions about our present and future? By taking this course, you can be part of the global conversation.  Climate Change: The Science is an introduction to climate science basics. We’ll discuss flows of energy and carbon in Earth’s climate system, how climate models work, climate history, and future forecasts. This course will give you the knowledge you need, and practice communicating about climate change. You’ll meet people from around the world with a huge range of local and regional climate change issues. Join us, learn the science, and share your own stories. ', 'https://edx.org/course/climate-change-science-ubcx-climate1x', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/r9mopioqk-8?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-10-14', 49, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/climate1x_banner.jpg?itok=CwCZStiP', 'Science', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'UBCx', '2015-11-24 23:09:30'),
(3120, 'Coaching for Performance', 'Managers are charged with managing several people and supporting successful outcomes.', 'Managers are charged with managing several people and supporting successful outcomes. They have not had specific instruction and practice in core coaching skills, and may not be sure how to apply them to actual work situations.', 'https://novoed.com/Coaching-for-Performance-Fall-2015', '', '2015-09-28', 41, '', '', 'NovoEd', 225, 'English', 'yes', '', '2015-11-24 23:09:29'),
(3121, 'Cognitive technologies: The real opportunities for business', 'Artificial intelligence (AI) may sound like science fiction, but it is real, and becoming increasingly important to companies in every sector.', 'Artificial intelligence (AI) may sound like science fiction, but it is real, and becoming increasingly important to companies in every sector. The field of artificial intelligence has produced a wide variety of "cognitive technologies" that simulate human reasoning and perceptual skills, giving businesses entirely new capabilities and enabling organizations to break prevailing tradeoffs between speed, cost, and quality.', 'https://novoed.com/cognitive-technology', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/aJMNsyQA79Y?vq=auto&rel=0&showinfo=0&autohide=1&wmode=transparent&origin=https://novoed.com', '2015-10-19', 50, '', '', 'NovoEd', -1, 'English', 'no', 'Deloitte University Press', '2015-11-24 23:09:29'),
(3122, 'College Algebra and Problem Solving', 'In this college level Algebra course, you will learn to apply algebraic reasoning to solve problems effectively.', 'In this college level Algebra course, you will learn to apply algebraic reasoning to solve problems effectively. You’ll develop skills in linear and quadratic functions, general polynomial functions, rational functions, and exponential and logarithmic functions. You will also study systems of linear equations. This course will emphasize problem-solving techniques, specifically by means of discussing concepts in each of these topics. Content in this course will be adaptive, allowing you to achieve mastery in a certain concept before moving on to the next. This 3 credit hour course satisfies the Mathematical Studies (MA) general studies requirement at Arizona State University. This course may satisfy a general education requirement at other institutions; however, it is strongly encouraged that you consult with your institution of choice to determine how these credits will be applied to their degree requirements prior to transferring the credit. ', 'https://edx.org/course/college-algebra-problem-solving-asux-mat117-credit-eligible', '', '2016-03-14', 56, '', 'Math', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'ASUx', '2015-11-24 23:09:30'),
(3123, 'Combinatorial Mathematics 组合数学', 'Our lives are full of combinations.', 'Our lives are full of combinations. Combinatorial mathematics is just the science to deal with combinations of discrete items. As an ancient field, the history of combinatorial mathematics can be traced back over 4000 years to the age of the Great Yu in ancient China. Today, combinatorial mathematics is regarded as the basis of computer science since the algorithms in programming heavily rely on the analysis of the discrete elements. FAQ I don’t speak Chinese, can I learn the course? All the materials are in English. Though the original video was recorded in Chinese, the course team record the corresponding dubbing in English. All the audio and subtitles are processed to fit the English dubbing as much as possible, so that you can enjoy this wonderful course in English. What are the textbook and the reference books for this course? There is no textbook requirement for this course. The handouts distributed every week are critical. The following books are references What is the grading breakdown? How can I get the certificate? If your final score is no less than 60. Do I need to know how to program to learn this class? Not necessary. This course is a math course which is based on fundamental theory. But to help the students to have the intuitive feel of the effects of the theory, we also provide a code lib that you can compare different implementations by running different programs.     ', 'https://edx.org/course/combinatorial-mathematics-zu-he-shu-xue-tsinghuax-60240013x', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/i0egb-QskVs?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-10-01', 84, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/combinatorial-mathematics_378x225.jpg?itok=Cuq3uIdF', 'Math', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'TsinghuaX', '2015-11-24 23:09:30'),
(3124, 'Communicating Strategically', 'Far too frequently, the people who have the most to say have the hardest time saying it.', 'Far too frequently, the people who have the most to say have the hardest time saying it. Many of the best minds in our society, our most talented employees and our most promising students, fail to have the impact they could because of ineffective strategies for communicating their ideas and insights to others. This five-week refresher is geared toward experts (scientists, engineers, and other technical professionals) and will help them effectively communicate with non-scientists, usually management, to inform organizational decision-making. Join us as we examine and learn the essential components of communication strategy. ', 'https://edx.org/course/communicating-strategically-purduex-pn-15-2', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/m8QCcQxx2LM?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2015-11-24', 35, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/pn-15.2-communicating_strategically-course_image-378x225b.png?itok=Yfe5NA25', 'Communication', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'PurdueX', '2015-11-24 23:09:30'),
(3125, 'Compliance in Office 365: eDiscovery', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning.', 'EdX keeps courses open for enrollment after they end to allow learners to explore content and continue learning. All features and materials may not be all available. Check back often to see when new course start dates are announced.  In Compliance in Office 365: eDiscovery, you will examine how to plan, implement, and manage eDiscovery. As organizational data stored in email and documents continues to grow, Office 365 makes it easy to find the relevant information as you need it. This training covers all the steps to effectively plan and manage discovery requests. This is the first in a series of courses concerning Compliance in Office 365. By completing this course, you will gain an understanding of the eDiscovery architecture and how to effectively implement and use eDiscovery in your organization ', 'https://edx.org/course/compliance-office-365-ediscovery-microsoft-cld204x', '', '2015-11-24', 28, '', 'Computer Science', 'edX', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Microsoft', '2015-11-24 23:09:30'),
(3126, 'Comprendre la respiration', 'Pourquoi respirons-nous ?', 'Pourquoi respirons-nous ? A quoi servent nos poumons ? Quel est le lien entre l’oxygène et la vie ? Ces questions ouvrent un vaste champ de découvertes et de curiosités pour mieux comprendre la  respiration. Ce cours s’adresse à toute personne qui souhaite apprivoiser, s’approprier ou approfondir le fonctionnement de la respiration et des poumons, autrement dit la physiologie respiratoire humaine.   Plongés au cœur de l’université et de la pratique hospitalière, durant  quatre semaines, vous côtoierez professeurs, professionnels de la santé, internes et étudiants de médecine. Vous y apprendrez des notions de niveau universitaire qui ont été sélectionnées et adaptées afin que toute personne intéressée puisse les comprendre et y donner du sens. Ainsi, nous aborderons des thèmes proches du monde qui vous entoure : la respiration lors d’un effort physique, en altitude, le rôle des polluants atmosphériques, l’asthme….   A chaque leçon, un expert abordera des domaines concrets et pratiques : comment apprécier l’oxygénation d’un patient, pourquoi lui administrer de l’oxygène, que signifie hyperventiler….   Ce cours vous fera entrer en profondeur dans un monde où l’atmosphère est faite d’anatomie humaine, de physique des volumes et des pressions, de gaz et de sang, d’oxygène et de CO2, de poumons et de tissus, de tabagisme et de bronchite chronique.   Au terme de ce cours, vous serez capables de Bref, vous aurez, pour votre plaisir et votre motivation, approfondi votre culture générale en acquérant des connaissances élevées. Table des matières : Semaine 1 Semaine 2 Semaine 3 Semaine 4 ', 'https://edx.org/course/comprendre-la-respiration-louvainx-louv8x-0', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/36jSPFQViOM?version=3&amp;autohide=1', '2016-02-29', 28, 'https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/styles/course_video_banner/public/course/image/featured-card/comprendre-la-respiration_378x225.jpg?itok=IptRI2ra', 'Biology & Life Sciences', 'edX', 0, 'Français', 'yes', 'LouvainX', '2015-11-24 23:09:30');
