(4369, '中國人文經典導讀 | Classics of Chinese Humanities: Guided Readings', '本課程對象為對中國文化有興趣的同學。\n課程目的為通過四個不同特色的主題，討論中國文化的四個主要面向。每個主題選取兩篇經典文本作為核心閱讀，並與延伸閱讀做互文探討，以新角度解讀經典文本的意義，展現中國文化的複雜性、多元性。文本難度與大學一年級國文程度相當。', '本課程對象為對中國文化有興趣的同學。\n課程目的為通過四個不同特色的主題，討論中國文化的四個主要面向。每個主題選取兩篇經典文本作為核心閱讀，並與延伸閱讀做互文探討，以新角度解讀經典文本的意義，展現中國文化的複雜性、多元性。文本難度與大學一年級國文程度相當。', 'https://class.coursera.org/chinesehumanities-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=', '2014-04-24', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/a5/c14102371930437cc47e4107f14e0b/humanities.jpg', 'Humanities ,', 'Coursera', 0, 'Chinese', 'no', 'The Chinese University of Hong Kong,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4371, 'Growing Old Around the Globe', 'The world is ageing – people are older and societies are facing hard realities.  What are we to make our lives in this time of global ageing? In six weeks, we analyze critical questions about age and ageing around the world.', 'The world is ageing – people are older and societies are facing hard realities.  What are we to make our lives in this time of global ageing? In six weeks, we analyze critical questions about age and ageing around the world.', 'https://class.coursera.org/oldglobe-002/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ls5wfHfKO7Y', '2014-05-19', 7, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/41/0a3977d20447a8dd13dfa77ae1b95c/Kagan-Intro-fancy-back-16.png', 'Medicine,Health & Society,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of Pennsylvania,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4376, 'Introduction to Classical Music', 'This course will focus on Western classical music of the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries; it is designed for people who are passionate about classical music but who have not necessarily had any advanced training or taken any college-level music courses.  The only prerequisite is a basic knowledge of how to read musical notation.', 'This course will focus on Western classical music of the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries; it is designed for people who are passionate about classical music but who have not necessarily had any advanced training or taken any college-level music courses.  The only prerequisite is a basic knowledge of how to read musical notation.', 'https://class.coursera.org/introtoclassical-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hr_PIOV8T8w', '2015-11-18', 8, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/82/494840477311e5b3eed382ee851029/introclassical.png', 'Music, Film, and Audio,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of Michigan,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4378, 'Drug Discovery, Development & Commercialization ', 'Students will learn the process of drug discovery and development through specific examples of case studies to better understand the issues facing the challenges of delivering a new drug on the market. At the completion of this course you will be able to have a better understanding of how a small or large molecule becomes a pharmaceutical drug.', 'Students will learn the process of drug discovery and development through specific examples of case studies to better understand the issues facing the challenges of delivering a new drug on the market. At the completion of this course you will be able to have a better understanding of how a small or large molecule becomes a pharmaceutical drug.', 'https://class.coursera.org/drugdiscovery-002/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pJdVi_sLzh8', '2014-10-03', 9, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/19/623ca2e7f8e7f6810168e995c56af5/IR.jpg', 'Medicine,Biology & Life Sciences,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of California, San Diego,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4380, 'Social Epidemiology', 'Social epidemiology is about how a society makes people sick and/or healthy. We address not only the identification of new disease risk factors e.g., deficient social capital but also how well-known exposures e.g., cigarette smoking, lead paint, health insurance emerge and are maintained by the social system.', 'Social epidemiology is about how a society makes people sick and/or healthy. We address not only the identification of new disease risk factors e.g., deficient social capital but also how well-known exposures e.g., cigarette smoking, lead paint, health insurance emerge and are maintained by the social system.', 'https://class.coursera.org/socialepi-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rm8zQS3VbjQ', '2013-05-31', 7, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/45/b72d293518f08ce1ac1dc7fc1ffad2/Final-Social-Epidemiology-.jpg', 'Health & Society,Social Sciences,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of Minnesota,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4382, 'Interprofessional Healthcare Informatics ', 'This course examines the implications of informatics for practice, in nursing, public health, and healthcare in general. It covers electronic health record issues and relates ethical, legislative and political issues to health informatics. Students will also explore global and future informatics issues.', 'This course examines the implications of informatics for practice, in nursing, public health, and healthcare in general. It covers electronic health record issues and relates ethical, legislative and political issues to health informatics. Students will also explore global and future informatics issues.', 'https://class.coursera.org/newwayhealthcare-002/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZGiLIDrpZ-0', '2014-02-10', 10, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/d5/9752af8f689bbe28e9ace2e3a9054d/Final-Health-Informatics.jpg', 'Information, Tech & Design,Health & Society,Social Sciences,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of Minnesota,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4383, 'Sustainability of Food Systems: A Global Life Cycle Perspective', 'This course explores the diversity of the foods we eat, the ways in which we grow, process, distribute, and prepare them, and the impacts they have upon our environment, health, and society. We will also examine the challenges and opportunities of creating a more sustainable global food system in the future.', 'This course explores the diversity of the foods we eat, the ways in which we grow, process, distribute, and prepare them, and the impacts they have upon our environment, health, and society. We will also examine the challenges and opportunities of creating a more sustainable global food system in the future.', 'https://class.coursera.org/globalfoodsystems-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oXEePhCcr9g', '2013-06-14', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/7e/1ceb4e281dfe038babae68d58d5571/large.jpg', 'Economics & Finance,Food and Nutrition,Energy & Earth Sciences,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of Minnesota,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4384, 'Introduction to Thermodynamics: Transferring Energy from Here to There', 'In this course, you will learn how to characterize the energy state of a system and the mechanisms for transferring energy from one system to another.  These are the tools necessary to understand stationary and transportation power systems from small scale, like batteries, to large scale, like nuclear power plants.', 'In this course, you will learn how to characterize the energy state of a system and the mechanisms for transferring energy from one system to another.  These are the tools necessary to understand stationary and transportation power systems from small scale, like batteries, to large scale, like nuclear power plants.', 'https://class.coursera.org/introthermodynamics-008/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KC_9JH6PClo', '2015-11-18', 5, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/ba/be6840477311e5bbfd7500a1824fa5/thermodynamics.png', 'Engineering,Energy & Earth Sciences,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of Michigan,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4385, 'Calvin - Histoire et réception dune Réforme', 'Course in French with English subtitles --\n\nCe cours introduit à la vie et à la pensée du réformateur Jean Calvin 1509-1564 ainsi qu’à son influence sur le monde moderne et contemporain. La démarche proposée se veut critique, il ne s’agit ni de canoniser ni de condamner Calvin, mais de comprendre sa pensée avec toute la distance requise et d’en analyser les enjeux.\n--\nThis course is an introduction to the life and thought of the reformer John Calvin 1509-1564 and to his influence on the modern and contemporary world. The approach we develop is critical:  we intend neither to canonize nor to condemn Calvin or his thought. Our goal, rather, is to avoid any rash evaluation in order to understand his thought and analyze the issues at stake in it.', 'Course in French with English subtitles --\n\nCe cours introduit à la vie et à la pensée du réformateur Jean Calvin 1509-1564 ainsi qu’à son influence sur le monde moderne et contemporain. La démarche proposée se veut critique, il ne s’agit ni de canoniser ni de condamner Calvin, mais de comprendre sa pensée avec toute la distance requise et d’en analyser les enjeux.\n--\nThis course is an introduction to the life and thought of the reformer John Calvin 1509-1564 and to his influence on the modern and contemporary world. The approach we develop is critical:  we intend neither to canonize nor to condemn Calvin or his thought. Our goal, rather, is to avoid any rash evaluation in order to understand his thought and analyze the issues at stake in it.', 'https://class.coursera.org/calvin-002/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bc943ad0521511e5b00923c65f4349f0', '2015-10-23', 5, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/e5/1561248f3efdb3ed0e08c1b91de5fb/Calvin.jpg', 'Humanities ,', 'Coursera', 0, 'French', 'no', 'University of Geneva,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4393, 'Canine Theriogenology for Dog Enthusiasts', 'This course will help anyone who loves dogs to better understand their dog’s reproductive health and how to control its reproduction. This includes understanding the pros and cons of having your dog spayed or castrated, and understanding at what age that surgery can be performed.', 'This course will help anyone who loves dogs to better understand their dog’s reproductive health and how to control its reproduction. This includes understanding the pros and cons of having your dog spayed or castrated, and understanding at what age that surgery can be performed.', 'https://class.coursera.org/theriogenology-002/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gl0C5La-L1E', '2013-10-04', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/47/c5fdeff25af27747c79a1abaea75a8/Therio-logo.gif', 'Medicine,Health & Society,Biology & Life Sciences,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of Minnesota,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4394, 'Social and Economic Networks:  Models and Analysis', 'Learn how to model social and economic networks and their impact on human behavior.  How do networks form, why do they exhibit certain patterns, and how does their structure impact diffusion, learning, and other behaviors?   We will bring together models and techniques from economics, sociology, math, physics, statistics and computer science to answer these questions.  ', 'Learn how to model social and economic networks and their impact on human behavior.  How do networks form, why do they exhibit certain patterns, and how does their structure impact diffusion, learning, and other behaviors?   We will bring together models and techniques from economics, sociology, math, physics, statistics and computer science to answer these questions.  ', 'https://class.coursera.org/networksonline-004/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mjS81EoBQOU', '2015-09-18', 9, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/ec/50a9bcc99dfc058198c9d4827b11e7/Logo1.jpg', 'Computer Science: Theory,Economics & Finance,Mathematics,Statistics and Data Analysis,Social Sciences,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'Stanford University,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4405, 'The Role of the Renminbi in the International Monetary System ', 'This course will discuss various aspects of the Renminbi internationalization, including the reform of the international monetary system, the opportunities and challenges to internationalize the Renminbi, the evolution of Chinas monetary and exchange rate policies, and the implications of the Renminbi internationalization for Hong Kong.', 'This course will discuss various aspects of the Renminbi internationalization, including the reform of the international monetary system, the opportunities and challenges to internationalize the Renminbi, the evolution of Chinas monetary and exchange rate policies, and the implications of the Renminbi internationalization for Hong Kong.', 'https://class.coursera.org/renminbi-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KjtcIrDKUo0', '2013-09-30', 4, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/43/f60d61a66e46088b54c1384cb69619/renminbi.jpg', 'Economics & Finance,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'The Chinese University of Hong Kong,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
