(4705, 'Inquiry Science Learning: Perspectives & Practices 4 - Student-Centered Inquiry', 'In this course, teachers will develop the skills essential to move from a top-down content delivery model of science instruction to one in which the teacher is a guide, enabling students to create shared meaning of important science concepts.', 'In this course, teachers will develop the skills essential to move from a top-down content delivery model of science instruction to one in which the teacher is a guide, enabling students to create shared meaning of important science concepts.', 'https://class.coursera.org/scistudentinquiry-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nkn96rN-Aso', '2014-04-07', 4, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/e0/2c50b077cf8d982276008f3ef12a33/courseraLogo4.png', 'Education,Teacher Professional Development,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'Rice University,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
