(4709, 'Economics of Money and Banking, Part Two', 'Introduction to a “money view” of economic activity for modern times, building on the intellectual traditions of British central banking and American institutionalism. Part One explores the economics of payment systems and money markets. Part Two explores connections with foreign exchange and capital markets.  NOTE:  The first week of Part Two reviews Part One, so you can take Part Two even if you missed Part One.', 'Introduction to a “money view” of economic activity for modern times, building on the intellectual traditions of British central banking and American institutionalism. Part One explores the economics of payment systems and money markets. Part Two explores connections with foreign exchange and capital markets.  NOTE:  The first week of Part Two reviews Part One, so you can take Part Two even if you missed Part One.', 'https://class.coursera.org/money2-004/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a_oAv3k-2LQ', '2015-07-05', 7, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/63/bece9dad904bb5aa16ac3e511f5fb2/institute_pgm_1_600x340.jpg', 'Economics & Finance,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'Columbia University,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4720, 'Reason and Persuasion: Thinking Through Three Dialogues By Plato', 'In this course we will study Platos ancient art of blowing up your beliefs as you go, to make sure theyre built to last. We spend six weeks studying three Platonic dialogues, then two more weeks pondering a pair of footnotes to Plato; that is, we will consider some contemporary manifestations of issues Plato discusses. Our focus will be: moral theory and moral psychology. ', 'In this course we will study Platos ancient art of blowing up your beliefs as you go, to make sure theyre built to last. We spend six weeks studying three Platonic dialogues, then two more weeks pondering a pair of footnotes to Plato; that is, we will consider some contemporary manifestations of issues Plato discusses. Our focus will be: moral theory and moral psychology. ', 'https://class.coursera.org/reasonandpersuasion-002/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=43b8acd076fc11e4bd3a5d0390e46cec', '2015-01-12', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/2e/abd27b5ded8b660d20c3ae79c1a4d5/courselogo.jpg', 'Social Sciences,Arts,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'National University of Singapore,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4724, 'Asset Pricing, Part 1', 'This course is part one of a two-part introductory survey of graduate-level academic asset pricing. We will focus on building the intuition and deep understanding of how the theory works, how to use it, and how to connect it to empirical facts. This first part builds the basic theoretical and empirical tools around some classic facts. The second part delves more deeply into applications and empirical evaluation. \n', 'This course is part one of a two-part introductory survey of graduate-level academic asset pricing. We will focus on building the intuition and deep understanding of how the theory works, how to use it, and how to connect it to empirical facts. This first part builds the basic theoretical and empirical tools around some classic facts. The second part delves more deeply into applications and empirical evaluation. \n', 'https://class.coursera.org/assetpricing-003/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b2e18d4044f511e492d5cffbd9324138', '2015-06-08', 7, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/3d/ac88a052f511e4a50e27ce928f81ce/Dark-Blue.jpg', 'Economics & Finance,Mathematics,Business & Management,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'The University of Chicago,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
(4727, 'Advanced Instructional Strategies in the Virtual Classroom', 'Learn how to elevate your teaching by studying what some of the most successful  virtual teachers are doing to propel their students forward. We will investigate what teaching strategies make the biggest impact in virtual education, connect with innovative and experienced teachers, and apply core strategies to the key areas of K-12 virtual instruction.', 'Learn how to elevate your teaching by studying what some of the most successful  virtual teachers are doing to propel their students forward. We will investigate what teaching strategies make the biggest impact in virtual education, connect with innovative and experienced teachers, and apply core strategies to the key areas of K-12 virtual instruction.', 'https://class.coursera.org/advancedvirtual-004/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=15320340168811e48902bb314b00761a', '2015-09-28', 5, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/0c/cf6350378a11e4901f7529fd7259f3/LOGO2_noapple.png', '', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'University of California, Irvine,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
