(4749, 'Discrete Inference and Learning in Artificial Vision', 'We will present the state of the art energy minimization algorithms that are used to perform inference in modern artificial vision models: that is, efficient methods for obtaining the most likely interpretation of a given visual input. We will also cover the popular max-margin framework for estimating the model parameters using inference.', 'We will present the state of the art energy minimization algorithms that are used to perform inference in modern artificial vision models: that is, efficient methods for obtaining the most likely interpretation of a given visual input. We will also cover the popular max-margin framework for estimating the model parameters using inference.', 'https://class.coursera.org/artificialvision-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QPZeBdr3fHM', '2014-01-10', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/10/b69211826f81680acbbf763109177f/cours-nikos-3.jpg', 'Computer Science: Artificial Intelligence,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'CentraleSup�lec,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
