(5353, 'Wheels of Metals: Urban Mining for a Circular Economy', 'Population and welfare are growing. Providing the world with metals is becoming a major challenge. Only by closing the loop will metals be available in sufficient quantities, not just now but also in the future: urban mining, the substantial re-use and recycling of metals. In this MOOC we will explore the challenges related to metals supply, both scarcity and environmental impacts, and the conditions and consequences of a circular economy for metals, based on the reports of UNEPs International Resource Panel.', 'Population and welfare are growing. Providing the world with metals is becoming a major challenge. Only by closing the loop will metals be available in sufficient quantities, not just now but also in the future: urban mining, the substantial re-use and recycling of metals. In this MOOC we will explore the challenges related to metals supply, both scarcity and environmental impacts, and the conditions and consequences of a circular economy for metals, based on the reports of UNEPs International Resource Panel.', 'https://class.coursera.org/metals-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=27271e60e26b11e3b1065dc911bff180', '2014-10-13', 5, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/38/375fa07c3911e3856425588ec96c38/logo_MetalWheels.png', 'Physical & Earth Sciences,Education,Energy & Earth Sciences,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'Universiteit Leiden,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
