(6294, 'Fog Networks and the Internet of Things', 'This course teaches the fundamentals of Fog Networking, the network architecture that uses one or a collaborative multitude of end-user clients or near-user edge devices to carry out storage, communication, computation, and control in a network. It also teaches the key results in the design of the Internet of Things, including consumer and industrial applications. ', 'This course teaches the fundamentals of Fog Networking, the network architecture that uses one or a collaborative multitude of end-user clients or near-user edge devices to carry out storage, communication, computation, and control in a network. It also teaches the key results in the design of the Internet of Things, including consumer and industrial applications. ', 'https://class.coursera.org/fog-001/', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3bb8291053ad11e49b9ba916b58830db', '2015-03-02', 6, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/5e/4244604d6e11e49ba297232d865156/fog-logo.png', 'Computer Science: Software Engineering,Engineering,', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'no', 'Princeton University,', '2015-11-18 00:00:00'),
